{"type":"message","id":"2c364de9","parentId":"dbd5c0ed","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:25:19.574Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me now understand the complete picture and create a plan. The user wants everything running. Let me look at the document more carefully to see all the components that should be running, and then compare with reality.\n\nFrom the v2026.4.14 document, the key components are:\n1. Gateway (port 3100 in doc, 18789 in reality) - ✅ running\n2. v8 Router (3102) - need to check\n3. v8 Scorer (3103) - ✅ running\n4. v8 Classifier (3105) - ✅ running\n5. Hook System - ✅ deployed\n6. Cron Scheduler - available\n7. Task Orchestrator - in skills\n8. WebSocket Server - ✅ (18789)\n9. Canvas Host - ✅\n10. Skills System - ✅\n11. 三层记忆系统 - ✅\n12. ACP Protocol - ?\n13. Lobster Workflow - ?\n14. Task Flow - in skills\n15. Browser automation - not configured\n\n\n16. Active Memory, Context Engine, and other advanced features seem to be experimental or plugin-based\n\nThe version mismatch is the real issue here—the document is from 2026.4.14 but the current system is running 2026.3.13, which means several features described in the documentation either don't exist yet or work differently than documented. I should check the skill files for task orchestrator and look at the actual gateway implementation to understand what's really available versus what's aspirational.","thinkingSignature":"ae2d3489c71fadf3dc41e042bab27db49a0dabee54bfbcff17c0bc05ba057c8c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qfwvsw0ye33n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if 3102 and 3104 exist as services\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3102/api/score -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"test\"}' 2>&1 | head -3\necho \"---3102 above---\"\ncurl -s http://localhost:3104/ 2>&1 | head -3\necho \"---3104 above---\"\n# Check if there's a way to see all openclaw capabilities\nopenclaw plugins list 2>/dev/null | head -30 || echo \"p