{"type":"message","id":"c3ba4e5a","parentId":"9123ab85","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:26:39.501Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! The `openclaw-context-api` is trying to start on port 3106, but **the openclaw-listener is already using port 3106**. That's why it keeps crashing with EADDRINUSE.\n\nSo there are two services trying to use port 3106:\n1. `openclaw-context-api` - supposed to run on 3106\n2. `openclaw-listener` - already running on 3106\n\nThis is a configuration conflict. Let me check the context-api configuration to see if it should use a different port, or if the listener should not be using 3106.\n\nWait - actually looking at the systemctl status again:\n- `openclaw-listener` is PID 593 and it's running\n\n\n- `openclaw-context-api` is trying to start on the same port and failing\n\nSo these are two separate services that both want 3106. I need to figure out which one is actually supposed to be there, or if one of them is misconfigured.","thinkingSignature":"c9d25705b360f4ee286ac784d996b88ff9eae870ae7b91a83d17cfb845e5030f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_69af9nfja9dg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check the context-api service definition\ncat ~/.config/systemd/user/openclaw-context-api.service 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\ncat ~/.config/systemd/user/openclaw-listener.service 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42386,"output":276,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64300,"cost":{"input":0.0127158,"output":0.0003312,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01434528}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776428789986,"responseId":"063159f2609180aba285094b31cce270"}}
