{"type":"message","id":"52c54f90","parentId":"c56500ae","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:29:28.720Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The config directory is empty! This is a problem. Let me check the actual ports and see what the 3103 service is exposing.","thinkingSignature":"ebef371ff28d211344ddb9a71c396bc373cc339ec39d772c96f94541c959b8a7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jcm6v40btu4w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test what the 3103 service actually responds to\ncurl -s http://localhost:3103/ 2>&1 | head -5\necho \"---\"\ncurl -s http://localhost:3103/api/score -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"test\"}' 2>&1 | head -3\necho \"---\"\ncurl -s http://localhost:3103/health 2>&1 | head -3\necho \"---\"\n# Test if there's intent endpoint\ncurl -s http://localhost:3103/api/intent -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"test\"}' 2>&1 | head -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":47266,"output":203,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69107,"cost":{"input":0.0141798,"output":0.00024359999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01572168}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776428962679,"responseId":"06315aa381165facd8b6ae660c580e2a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5800c08b","parentId":"52c54f90","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:29:29.110Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jcm6v40btu4w_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<title>Error</title>\n---\n{\"score\":33,\"factors\":{\"logic\":0,\"risk\":0,\"duration\":2,\"resource\":0,\"uncertainty\":0,\"dependency\":0},\"recommendedStrategy\":\"STEP_ARCHIVE\",\"timeout\":60,\"_raw\":{\"total\":2,\"max\":18}}---\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n---\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":212,"aggregated":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<title>Error</title>\n---\n{\"score\":33,\"factors\":{\"logic\":0,\"risk\":0,\"duration\":2,\"resource\":0,\"uncertainty\":0,\"dependency\":0},\"recommendedStrategy\":\"STEP_ARCHIVE\",\"timeout\":60,\"_raw\":{\"total\":2,\"max\":18}}---\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n---\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776428969042}}
{"type":"message","id":"478e9fa6","parentId":"5800c08b","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:29:55.986Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the 3103 service:\n- Has a `/api/score` endpoint ✅\n- Has a `/health` endpoint ✅\n- Does NOT have an `/api/intent` endpoint ❌\n- Root returns an error page\n\nThis is the v8 TaskOrchestrator. But the openclaw-listener config expects:\n- `http://localhost:3102/api/intent`\n- `http://localhost:3102/api/score`\n\nThe listener is pointing to 3102 but the actual scoring service is on 3103. This is a configuration mismatch.\n\nLet me now check if there's supposed to be a service on 3102 that provides the intent endpoint. The v8 TaskOrchestrator has a scoring endpoint but no intent endpoint. Maybe the intent detection was a feature that was removed or changed.\n \nI'm noticing something odd though - the 3105 classifier returns `scene: clarify` which is a routing decision, not a true intent classification like the old `/api/intent` endpoint was supposed to do. It looks like the intent detection functionality has been replaced by the scene classifier on 3105, but the listener is still configured to look for the old `/api/intent` endpoint on 3102.\n\nThis is a fundamental architectural mismatch. The v8.TaskOrchestrator on 3103 has the scoring adapter that `/api/score` calls, but there's no service actually running on 3102 where the listener expects it. And the scene classifier is only being called directly by hooks, not through the listener's routing logic. So the message flow isn't going through the intended pipeline at all - the hooks are working around the missing listener configuration rather than being properly integrated into it. The context-api keeps restarting over and over—that's 5111 restarts trying to bind to port 3106, but the listener already has it occupied. That's a resource leak and indicates a misconfiguration. The wiki-learn cron job is also failing with a 401 authentication error on what looks like a Feishu API call, so the secret key isn't being passed correctly in the request headers. I need to figure out what the old Windows system's architecture actually had running to understand why these services are conflicting now.\n\nLooking at the port mappings, the old system had Gateway on 3100, v8.router (TaskOrchestrator) on 3102 with both intent and score endpoints, scene-classifier on 3105, context-api on 3106, and the listener connecting to 3102. The current Linux system shifted everything—the Gateway is now on 18789, v8.TaskOrchestrator moved to 3103 without an intent endpoint, scene-classifier is still on 3105, but context-api can't start because the listener is using 3106, and the listener is still trying to connect to 3102 which doesn't exist. There's also an openclaw-listener process that appears to be something separate from the main services.\n\nThe listener is configured to use port 3102 for the gateway WebSocket connection, but that's not where the gateway is running—it's on 18789. So the listener can't actually connect to the gateway. This suggests either the configuration was updated to point to the right port but the service wasn't restarted, or there's a version mismatch between what the listener expects and what's actually running. The real question is whether the old Windows system was using port 3102 as the gateway port or if that's where the TaskOrchestrator was running, because right now the gateway at 18789 seems to be working fine based on the earlier test.\n\nThe critical issues to fix are that the listener has been pointing to the wrong gateway port this entire time, which means it's not even connected, and there's a conflicting service trying to use port 3106 where the listener is already running. There's also a cron job failing due to missing API authentication. Before diving into fixes, I should examine what the current openclaw gateway configuration actually specifies for the port, and then compare that against the v2026.4.14 framework document to see what the intended architecture was supposed to be.","thinkingSignature":"962ee8e6aefdfb077d961020bf093e7f35a4bbc8b077dbebe7296d5bf3284d62"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kpk0rwqyz6ej_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 关键：检查 gateway 的真实端口配置\ncat ~/.openclaw/config.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | grep -A5 \"gateway\\|port\\|listen\"\necho \"---\"\n# 检查 gateway 配置有没有端口设置\ncat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | grep -A10 \"gateway\\|port\\|listen\\|http\" | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":47588,"output":951,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70177,"cost":{"input":0.0142764,"output":0.0011412,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01671588}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776428969112,"responseId":"06315aa860dc15ca85d147315e18860e"}}
