{"type":"message","id":"def4c15a","parentId":"a194ac07","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:50:46.410Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Key findings:\n1. **3100**: LISTEN on *:3100 (Gateway!)\n2. **3102**: NOT running (the v8 Router that the docs say is inside Gateway)\n3. **3103**: LISTEN on 0.0.0.0:3103 (v8 scorer)\n4. **3105**: LISTEN on 0.0.0.0:3105 (scene classifier)\n5. **18789**: LISTEN on 127.0.0.1:18789 and [::1]:18789 (Gateway)\n6. **3106**: LISTEN on 127.0.0.1:3106 (openclaw-listener, after fix)\n\n\n7. The docs claim Gateway runs on 3100, but my earlier netstat showed port 18789 instead—that's the actual WebSocket port, not 3100. So either the documentation is outdated or 3100 is configured for something else. Let me verify what's actually listening on 3100.","thinkingSignature":"d12113ed46687c8009c6df2ea47487da8f79ac764fe61a6083134b00283e1ef2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ffstvsl90dzv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查3100是什么\necho \"=== 3100 进程 ===\"\nss -tlnp 2>/dev/null | grep 3100\nlsof -i :3100 2>/dev/null | head -5\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Gateway 版本精确 ===\"\ncurl -s http://127.0.0.1:18789/ 2>/dev/null | head -3\ncurl -s http://127.0.0.1:18789/__openclaw__/status 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('version:', d.get('version','?'))\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"status endpoint not found\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== active cron jobs ===\"\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43222,"output":400,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65260,"cost":{"input":0.0129666,"output":0.00047999999999999996,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01474488}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776430235756,"responseId":"06315f9abaebec7a911bbf3eb3637ca3"}}
