{"type":"message","id":"0ced9e97","parentId":"9e5ec2a9","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:52:39.088Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! TaskFlows has 115 items in **mirrored** mode. This means these are external tasks being observed, not managed by OpenClaw's Task Flow system. They show as \"task_mirrored\" which means they're observing external tasks.\n\nNow let me check:\n1. Browser plugin - loaded but no config (empty `{}`)2. Edge CDP - not accessible (no Edge running)\n3. Active Memory - DISABLED\n4. Lobster - DISABLED5. Context Engine - not installed (no lossless-claw)Let me now compile the full comparison.","thinkingSignature":"bc169a31a36aeaab70024dd504ae7ac9d971a777fb793ffa18a7ca9848d52b78"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zaw2k8hfuoni_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check memory provider config\necho \"=== memory provider ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nmem = d.get('memory',{})\nprint(json.dumps(mem, indent=2))\n\" 2>/dev/null\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== memory-lancedb ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nplugins = d.get('plugins',{}).get('entries',{})\nlancedb = plugins.get('memory-lancedb',{})\nprint(json.dumps(lancedb, indent=2))\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49316,"output":290,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71244,"cost":{"input":0.014794799999999999,"output":0.000348,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.016441079999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776430351043,"responseId":"0631600e0ef3713f1212e5febb1a8d39"}}
