{"type":"message","id":"87307926","parentId":"928c2ca4","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:57:25.739Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jbkup6m1ewr6_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Config warnings:\\n- plugins.entries.memory-lancedb: plugin disabled (disabled in config) but config is present\n\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.15 (041266a) — No $999 stand required.\n\nUsage: openclaw config set [options] [path] [value]\n\nSet config values by path (value mode, ref/provider builder mode, or batch JSON\nmode).\nExamples:\nopenclaw config set gateway.port 19001 --strict-json\nopenclaw config set channels.discord.token --ref-provider default --ref-source\nenv --ref-id DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN\nopenclaw config set secrets.providers.vault --provider-source file\n--provider-path /etc/openclaw/secrets.json --provider-mode json\nopenclaw config set --batch-file ./config-set.batch.json --dry-run\n\nArguments:\n  path                                  Config path (dot or bracket notation)\n  value                                 Value (JSON/JSON5 or raw string)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3225,"aggregated":"Config warnings:\\n- plugins.entries.memory-lancedb: plugin disabled (disabled in config) but config is present\n\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.15 (041266a) — No $999 stand required.\n\nUsage: openclaw config set [options] [path] [value]\n\nSet config values by path (value mode, ref/provider builder mode, or batch JSON\nmode).\nExamples:\nopenclaw config set gateway.port 19001 --strict-json\nopenclaw config set channels.discord.token --ref-provider default --ref-source\nenv --ref-id DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN\nopenclaw config set secrets.providers.vault --provider-source file\n--provider-path /etc/openclaw/secrets.json --provider-mode json\nopenclaw config set --batch-file ./config-set.batch.json --dry-run\n\nArguments:\n  path                                  Config path (dot or bracket notation)\n  value                                 Value (JSON/JSON5 or raw string)","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776430645674}}
{"type":"message","id":"1c83bf47","parentId":"87307926","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:57:34.204Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can use `openclaw config set` with a path and value. For batch changes, there's a `--batch-file` option. But I'd need to create a file. Alternatively, I can make multiple calls.\n\nLet me try setting both at once with a JSON value. The path would be `plugins.entries.active-memory` and the value would be `{\"enabled\": true}`.\n\nActually, looking at the help, it says \"batch JSON mode\". Let me check if I can do it with a single JSON string. The issue is that the shell will have trouble with JSON values containing quotes.\n\nLet me try:\n```bash\nopenclaw config set 'plugins.entries.active-memory' '{\"enabled\":true}'\nopenclaw config set 'plugins.entries.lobster' '{\"enabled\":true}'\n\n\n```\n\nOr maybe I can use `--batch-file` with a temporary JSON file instead.","thinkingSignature":"8c012ca72570f0d834053932322d5d1c0aa3c04a70fb210e2761e741e13d5a8e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qxam5v9rt5ev_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/openclaw-plugins-batch.json","content":"[\n  { \"path\": \"plugins.entries.active-memory\", \"value\": { \"enabled\": true } },\n  { \"path\": \"plugins.entries.lobster\", \"value\": { \"enabled\": true } }\n]\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":44544,"output":263,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66445,"cost":{"input":0.013363199999999999,"output":0.0003156,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014977079999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776430645740,"responseId":"06316135d6da46705f8e87a0b375a6d2"}}
