{"type":"message","id":"35090711","parentId":"a76023d7","timestamp":"2026-04-17T13:03:19.865Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The browser plugin config schema is empty - no configuration options. Let me check if there's a way to configure it through the main openclaw config under `plugins.entries.browser`.\n\nLet me check if there's a browser configuration in openclaw.json.\n\nActually, looking at the docs more carefully:\n- Browser automation uses Windows Edge because of China restrictions\n- We have chromium-browser in WSL but the OpenClaw browser plugin is designed for Edge on Windows\n\nThe browser plugin is loaded but there's no browser running for it to use. This is an environmental limitation.\n\nLet me move on to what's actually fixable:1. ✅ Active Memory - FIXED\n2. ✅ Lobster - FIXED\n3. Context Engine - Built-in, no plugin needed\n\n\n4. Browser - Env limitation (Edge only), not fixable from WSL\n5. Task Flow - 115 flows exist, they're mirrored from external agents, the \"managed\" flows might need a different setup\n\nLet me focus on Task Flow next. The document says \"Task Flow Managed\" but the flows are all \"task_mirrored\" mode, which means they're observation mirrors of external agents rather than directly managed tasks. I need to understand what creates managed Task Flows versus mirrored ones.\n\nActually, I'm realizing I should concentrate on what's practically fixable. The Context Engine appears to be built-in architecture rather than a plugin, and while the browser plugin is loaded, it can't function without Windows Edge. Let me verify the current status of the remaining items: Active Memory and Lobster are now enabled, and I need to check the羊毛系统 which appears to have 21 skills installed and 2363 lines across various files.","thinkingSignature":"dd7ddcbd69f29b39e6796cb9a97d70183444613478ffb7c4ca572003e8c32abf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_axstdhbqx20t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"#