{"type":"message","id":"44bb1975","parentId":"e7dfa4c4","timestamp":"2026-04-17T13:04:47.098Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! The agent-browser works with the local Chromium! \"百度一下，你就知道\" means Baidu's homepage loaded successfully. \n\nSo browser automation IS working - just using local Chromium in WSL instead of Windows Edge.\n\nNow, the OpenClaw browser plugin is loaded, and we have a working browser automation tool. The docs described Windows Edge but Chromium works fine in WSL.\n\nNow let me think about what's left to fix:1. ✅ Active Memory - FIXED\n2. ✅ Lobster - FIXED\n3. ✅ Browser automation - FIXED (local Chromium)4. Context Engine - Built-in, working\n5. Task Flow - Need to understand what \"managed\" means\n\n\n6. The 115 existing flows are mirrored from external agents rather than directly managed workflows, but since Lobster (the typed workflow engine) is now enabled and loaded, I should check whether Task Flow itself requires Lobster to function properly or if it's a separate system entirely.","thinkingSignature":"2885315169a2d4e248c01abc78f3d45c04c71ddae7318c9af923359fd85f302c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g8s9qyin074l_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check Task Flow - what does \"managed\" mean?\nnode ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/openclaw.mjs tasks flow --help 2>&1 | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48946,"output":267,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70851,"cost":{"input":0.014683799999999999,"output":0.0003204,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.016302479999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776431078243,"responseId":"063162e424c3a4c92fd4423071c167e7"}}
