{"type":"message","id":"b2bb4640","parentId":"67e469ff","timestamp":"2026-04-17T14:22:36.511Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The listener is in a constant reconnect loop. Every 10 seconds the gateway closes the WebSocket connection (code 1000), and the listener immediately reconnects. This is the #1 functional problem.\n\nThe listener is PID 149465, which is the node process for the listener. The gateway (PID 153280) is closing the connection every 10 seconds. This is likely the gateway's idle timeout or max connection age logic.\n\nLet me check the listener source code to understand why this might be happening. But first, let me also check if the listener is actually doing anything useful. Looking at the config - `reply.enabled: false` - it seems the listener is not processing messages back to anywhere important.\n\n\nActually, the real question is what the listener is supposed to do in this setup. It's receiving gateway WebSocket connections, but since `reply.enabled: false`, it's not sending anything back. The auto-score-classify hook runs on the gateway side anyway, so the listener might just be redundant in this architecture.\n\nThe constant disconnections suggest the gateway is enforcing a 10-second idle timeout, possibly as part of its local token validation or connection management. Since the listener reconnects immediately, the queue database should theoretically stay synced, but I need to understand what the listener is actually trying to accomplish here.\n\nLet me prioritize the most critical issues to address: the listener's WebSocket stability is the main concern, though it might be expected behavior if this is a gateway-level idle timeout. The other significant finding is that 3100 appears to be an undocumented port - it's listening but not obviously tied to OpenClaw or any known service, which warrants investigation. The listener's continuous reconnect loop is the primary issue here—it's cycling every 10 seconds when it should maintain a persistent connection, suggesting either a gateway idle timeout or a misconfiguration in how the listener establishes its WebSocket connection to the gateway. I should also check whether the listener actually needs to be running at all, since it's supposed to feed into a scoring system that may not even exist anymore.","thinkingSignature":"250ef5ee9aedbcf52bd30cedc9da5f60ebf9b860dc64b193943b0dffaa5fcb2b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s90pfw6p0dg5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 21. Listener 源码分析 ===\"\ngrep -r \"heartbeat\\|idle\\|timeout\\|maxAge\\|close\" /home/ai/openclaw-listener/src/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".js.map\" | grep -v \"node_modules\" | head -20\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 22. 检查 listener 是否需要 gateway ws keepalive ===\"\ngrep -A5 -B5 \"heartbeatInterval\\|ping\\|pong\" /home/ai/openclaw-listener/config.json 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":66959,"output":554,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89151,"cost":{"input":0.0200877,"output":0.0006648,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02205078}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776435741787,"responseId":"0631751c3d5514f25c8dfa8bda49fb89"}}
