{"type":"message","id":"097f21c6","parentId":"de1722b1","timestamp":"2026-04-17T14:22:53.352Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue! Looking at the gatewayClient.ts:\n\n```javascript\nthis.ws.on('close', this.onClose.bind(this));\nif (this.heartbeatTimer) clearInterval(this.heartbeatTimer);\nthis.heartbeatTimer = setInterval(() => {\n}, this.config.heartbeatInterval);\n```\n\nWait - the heartbeatTimer is set to fire every `heartbeatInterval` (30000ms = 30 seconds). But the connection is closing after only 10 seconds. So the heartbeat is NOT the cause.\n\nThe issue is in `main.ts`:\n```javascript\ngatewayClient.on('close', (code, reason) => {\n    logger.warn({ code, reason: reason?.toString() }, 'Gateway connection closed');\n    gatewayClient.close();  // <-- This closes the listener-side connection too!\n    if (queue) await queue.close();\n});\n```\n\nWait, `gatewayClient.close()` is called when the close event is received from the gateway. That's odd - why would the listener close its own side when the gateway closes? This looks like it could be a bug. When the gateway closes the WebSocket, the listener receives the close event, logs it, but then calls `gatewayClient.close()` which seems redundant since the connection is already closed.\n\nActually, let me look at the flow more carefully. The gateway closes the connection (code 1000), the listener's WebSocket 'close' event fires, and then `gatewayClient.close()` is called - but the connection is already closed at that point, so this might just be a no-op or there could be some cleanup happening.\n\nThe real issue is that the gateway is closing the connection every 10 seconds, which seems intentional. This might be the gateway's design to enforce reconnection periodically. The listener is handling it correctly by reconnecting. Let me check if the 3100 port is the Control UI HTTP server.\n\nWait - the listener is configured to use port 3106 for its health server, but I'm seeing 3100 listening instead. I should check what process is actually listening on 3100.","thinkingSignature":"b53d25621e194103019eff48cfee8279e529766263c95fa1bcb76399dcfe9ed0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y4bynae0wyyv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 23. 3100 端口深度追溯 ===\"\nss -tlnp | grep 3100\nfuser 3100/tcp 2>/dev/null || echo \"fuser not available\"\ncat /proc/net/tcp6 2>/dev/null | awk '\nBEGIN { FS=\" \"; CONVFMT=\"%.8x\" }\n$2 ~ /00000000:0C18$/ { print \"Local address:\", $2, \"Local port:\", $4 }\n' 2>/dev/null || echo \"awk failed\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":68123,"output":565,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90326,"cost":{"input":0.020436899999999997,"output":0.000678,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.022413179999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776435756895,"responseId":"0631752ce21a02b50dbcfbf1f1c815be"}}
