{"type":"message","id":"00cfc302","parentId":"84d40783","timestamp":"2026-04-17T14:23:52.577Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - 3100 returns \"404 page not found\" which means it's an HTTP server. It could be the gateway's HTTP interface (not WebSocket). But the gateway is supposed to be on 18789...\n\nActually, wait. Looking at the ports:- 127.0.0.1:18789 - Gateway WebSocket- [::1]:18789 - Gateway WebSocket (IPv6)\n- 127.0.0.1:3106 - Listener health server- *:3100 - Something else (HTTP, returns 404)\n\nThis 3100 HTTP server returning \"404 page not found\" is odd. \n\nSo the Gateway binds to 18789 for both WebSocket and HTTP, which means that 3100 port responding with a 404 is likely something else entirely—maybe a WSL system service or another container—but it's not the gateway itself since that's already on 18789.\n\nLooking at the session summary, the 3100 service was already running before openclaw started, so it's probably unrelated to the gateway. The \"404 page not found\" response suggests it might be an HTTP server, but it's not the gateway since the session output confirms the gateway is only listening on 18789.\n\nLet me wrap up the critical findings: the listener WebSocket keeps reconnecting every 10 seconds due to what looks like a gateway idle timeout, and the scene classifier is returning oddly formatted LLM responses instead of the expected structure. The 3100 port appears to be an external service unrelated to openclaw. Most concerning is the listener's idle timeout behavior—I should check if there's a way to configure it from the gateway side. For the scene classifier, the response structure seems technically valid even if the formatting is unusual, so that's lower priority. I've already fixed the config issues from earlier. The main outstanding problem is that the listener keeps reconnecting to the gateway every 10 seconds instead of maintaining a persistent connection. Looking at the listener's main.ts, when it receives a 'close' event from the gateway, it also calls `gatewayClient.close()` on its own end, which might be triggering additional cleanup or reconnection logic that's causing this looping behavior. I see the flow now - when the gateway closes the connection, the listener's `onClose` callback fires and logs the close event, but the gatewayClient is already in a closed state at that point, so calling `close()` again is just a no-op. The `ws.on('close', this.onClose.bind(this))` handler is set up to catch when the gateway actually closes the connection, and the reconnect logic should handle recovering from this. I'm realizing there might be a bug in how the listener handles the connection closure - specifically in `gatewayClient.ts`, the listener is registering a close event handler, but there could be an issue with how it processes the close code and reason when the gateway terminates the connection.\n\nLooking at the flow more carefully: the gateway closes the WebSocket (code 1000, reason \"\"), which triggers the listener's `on('close')` handler, which emits its own close event with the same code and reason. Then in `main.ts`, when that close event fires, the listener tries to call `close()` again on an already-closed client, which might be harmless or might indicate the reconnect isn't being handled properly.\n\nRather than dig deeper into the source code, I should step back and assess whether this reconnect loop is actually causing real problems or if it's just normal behavior that I need to accept.","thinkingSignature":"c11c6aaf4316c40ea81b861148a14bece740361d634546f06b0831e0831e22c7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0fc9mcff7hsj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 29. Listener queue 持久化验证 ===\"\nls -la /tmp/openclaw-listener-queue.db 2>/dev/null\necho \"数据库大小: $(wc -c < /tmp/openclaw-listener-queue.db 2>/dev/null || echo 0) bytes\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 30. 对比 Listener 日志中的连接时长 ===\"\npython3 -c \"\nimport json\ntimes = []\nwith open('/tmp/openclaw-listener.log') as f:\n    for line in f:\n        try:\n            d = json.loads(line)\n            if 'WebSocket connected' in d.get('msg',''):\n                times.append(d['time'])\n            elif 'Gateway connection closed' in d.get('msg',''):\n                if times:\n                    from datetime import datetime\n                    t1 = datetime.fromisoformat(times[-1].replace('Z','+00:00'))\n                    t2 = datetime.fromisoformat(d['time'].replace('Z','+00:00'))\n                    print(f'Connected: {times[-1][-8:]} -> Closed: {d[\\\"time\\\"][-8:]} = {round((t2-t1).total_seconds())}s')\n        except: pass\n\" 2>/dev/null | tail -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69989,"output":1009,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92636,"cost":{"input":0.0209967,"output":0.0012108,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02350578}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776435806035,"responseId":"0631755c8b335a445e62116375c02a7c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8bddba5f","parentId":"00cfc302","timestamp":"2026-04-17T14:23:53.058Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0fc9mcff7hsj_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== 29. Listener queue 持久化验证 ===\n-rw-r--r-- 1 ai ai 12288 Apr 17 20:37 /tmp/openclaw-listener-queue.db\n数据库大小: 12288 bytes\n\n=== 30. 对比 Listener 日志中的连接时长 ===\nConnected: :01.213Z -> Closed: :08.930Z = 8s\nConnected: :09.932Z -> Closed: :19.935Z = 10s\nConnected: :20.939Z -> Closed: :28.329Z = 7s\nConnected: :29.332Z -> Closed: :39.335Z = 10s\nConnected: :40.338Z -> Closed: :50.342Z = 10s"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":241,"aggregated":"=== 29. Listener queue 持久化验证 ===\n-rw-r--r-- 1 ai ai 12288 Apr 17 20:37 /tmp/openclaw-listener-queue.db\n数据库大小: 12288 bytes\n\n=== 30. 对比 Listener 日志中的连接时长 ===\nConnected: :01.213Z -> Closed: :08.930Z = 8s\nConnected: :09.932Z -> Closed: :19.935Z = 10s\nConnected: :20.939Z -> Closed: :28.329Z = 7s\nConnected: :29.332Z -> Closed: :39.335Z = 10s\nConnected: :40.338Z -> Closed: :50.342Z = 10s","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776435832958}}
{"type":"message","id":"772873bb","parentId":"8bddba5f","timestamp":"2026-04-17T14:24:06.961Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the pattern clearly:- Connections last 7-10 seconds then are closed by the gateway\n- The gateway is enforcing a ~10 second idle timeout on WebSocket connections\n- The listener immediately reconnects after each closeThis is a **bug/issue in the gateway or listener configuration**. The gateway should NOT be closing WebSocket connections every 10 seconds. This causes:1. Unnecessary reconnect overhead2. Potential message replay issues3. Queue DB bloat from frequent disconnectsThe fix needs to be either:1. Configure the gateway to not close idle WebSocket connections (if possible)\n2. Configure the listener to send something to keep the connection alive (not just heartbeats every 30s)3. \n\nThe listener's heartbeat is set to 30 seconds but connections are dying after 7-10 seconds, so the heartbeat interval needs to be shorter to match the gateway's idle timeout. Alternatively, the gateway might have a maximum connection age limit that's forcibly closing connections. I should check if there's a gateway configuration option like `gateway.ws.maxConnectionAge` or similar settings that could be causing this. Let me look at the listener's source to see if there's something I'm missing about how it should be maintaining the connection.\n\nActually, I need to reconsider - the listener is a gateway bridge, so if the gateway is the one closing connections, there's likely an authentication or session validation happening that's timing out. The listener has a valid token and connects successfully, but then gets disconnected after 10 seconds, which suggests the issue is on the gateway side rather than the listener configuration.\n\nWait, I should check the gateway configuration file - there might be settings like `maxConnectionAge` or `maxSessionAge` that are forcing these closures.","thinkingSignature":"2244047801a9b7cb75511e94cb1e4a8e219a07e9f325abd4ee5a131f3c06b6cb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jzdxbmzjw9q4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\ngw = d.get('gateway',{})\n# Print all gateway settings\nfor k,v in gw.items():\n    if k != 'auth':\n        print(f'{k}: {json.dumps(v) if isinstance(v,dict) else v}')\nprint('---')\nauth = gw.get('auth',{})\nprint(f'auth: {json.dumps(auth)}')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":71175,"output":476,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93289,"cost":{"input":0.0213525,"output":0.0005712,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02322198}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776435833060,"responseId":"0631757795bde4227c511254df36d4e6"}}
