{"type":"message","id":"272e28be","parentId":"fa8d1ff1","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:17:54.974Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway's `router/api.js` reads `config.context.maxContextTokens` and `config.context.summarizeThreshold` from the config. This means if I add a `context` section to openclaw.json, the gateway will use it.\n\nBut `v8/src/context/ContextProtector.js` is a standalone module that's NOT the same as `router/api.js`. The router uses these config values for something, but NOT for calling ContextProtector.js.\n\nLet me look at what the router does with these values.","thinkingSignature":"0e5a2194b5137e8274f9cf056a0c109dd430a5bce9e9fd7320f7c46ccc6608b1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wuus2xw042dd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -B5 -A20 \"maxContextTokens\\|summarizeThreshold\" ~/.openclaw/v8/src/router/api.js 2>/dev/null | head -50"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":95480,"output":166,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117284,"cost":{"input":0.028644,"output":0.0001992,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03014148}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776442669556,"responseId":"0631902d94703523e152e474708c46a3"}}
