{"type":"message","id":"03a9f9f5","parentId":"5b22e190","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:18:29.875Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The executor doesn't seem to have context assembly either. Let me look at the main gateway index.js or the agent runtime. Actually, the gateway might be calling out to an external LLM API directly with assembled messages.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The key insight is:\n- The gateway sends messages to the LLM API (e.g., Minimax)\n- The LLM API itself handles context window management (it only processes the last N tokens)\n- The gateway doesn't do any local context truncation\n\nSo the question is: what is the actual context management in the current system?\n\nThe answer is: **The LLM provider manages the context window.** The gateway just sends the full history and the provider truncates.\n \nTo properly implement context management, I'd need to intercept the message assembly before each LLM call, count tokens, and truncate if necessary. That would require modifying gateway code. Alternatively, I could enhance the existing ContextProtector in v8/src/context/ to actually get invoked, or build a simpler hook-based approach that compresses session history on a cadence. The protection middleware is a more robust solution, but it's not currently being used.\n\nLooking at the architecture more carefully, the real issue is that `v8/src/context/ContextProtector.js` has the right methods but isn't actually integrated into the message assembly flow, while `protection/` has a complete system with monitoring, detection, and compression, but it's running as a separate HTTP service on port 3002 that isn't being used. The practical approach would be to configure context settings for monitoring, start the protection middleware as a service to handle periodic checking and compression through the session management API, and potentially create a gateway hook that calls the context API before each LLM call. Let me check what endpoint the protection middleware actually calls when it performs compression.","thinkingSignature":"ec034328b81c9cb1fcec4a4d560e6abb6ac762aff29641a52615b34ac7783d1e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n185p5tq4eit_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"127.0.0.1:18789\\|GATEWAY\\|api.*call\\|/api/\" ~/.openclaw/protection/context_protector.js 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":96583,"output":435,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":118656,"cost":{"input":0.028974899999999998,"output":0.000522,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03079518}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776442695022,"responseId":"06319047a967fdf9795c44817e6aa2e6"}}
