{"type":"message","id":"aa7e3050","parentId":"94afed6f","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:19:11.684Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The v8 components use hardcoded defaults. The config.js in v8/src loads from non-existent YAML files. This means the v8 components use their default values.\n\nNow let me think about what to do. The user is asking why I haven't configured context management. The honest answer is:\n\n1. The context management code exists in multiple places but is not integrated\n2. The gateway doesn't have a built-in context truncation mechanism3. The v8 ContextProtector has the right logic but is never called\n4. The protection middleware is complete but not deployed\n\nLet me now build a proper solution. The most surgical approach:1. Create a `message:preprocessed` hook that:\n   - Checks session message count and total length   - If over threshold, triggers compaction (writes to session or calls a summary API)\n   - Updates the session with compacted history2. Configure context thresholds in openclaw.json3. Verify the hook worksActually, looking at this more practically - the simplest effective solution:1. Configure `context` in openclaw.json (for monitoring/alerting)2. Create a `session: compaction` hook that compacts session history when needed3. \n\nThe real issue is that context management needs to happen at the message assembly layer, not through hooks which are asynchronous and can't modify the current turn. But there's no such hook available anyway. The most practical approach is to configure context thresholds in openclaw.json, create a `message:preprocessed` hook for proactive detection, and test whether the existing `compact` command in the gateway actually works for manual compaction. I should just execute this rather than continuing to analyze.\n\nActually, I need to understand the current session state first - how many messages are in this session and how much context is being used - before I can determine the right context management strategy. Let me start by checking the actual session size.","thinkingSignature":"232cb68af0b1603880ff8a6f88cd7177a2f8b2c957ecbf0de7104fc30ce3b7f3"},{"type":"text","text":"先搞清楚当前 session 状态，再决定配置策略：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sqvvj9360hy0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 当前 session 消息数 ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/sessions/agent\\:main\\:main/context.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nmsgs = d.get('messages',[])\nprint(f'消息数: {len(msgs)}')\ntotal_chars = sum(len(m.get('content','')) for m in msgs)\nprint(f'总字符: {total_chars}')\n\" 2>/dev/null\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Compact 命令帮助 ===\"\nnode ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/openclaw.mjs compact --help 2>&1 | head -10\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 当前配置的 context 参数 ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nctx = d.get('context',{})\nprint(json.dumps(ctx, indent=2) if ctx else '{} (空)')\n\n# agents defaults\nagents = d.get('agents',{}).get('defaults',{}) if isinstance(d.get('agents'),dict) else {}\nprint('agents.defaults keys:', list(agents.keys())[:10])\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98180,"output":675,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120493,"cost":{"input":0.029453999999999998,"output":0.00081,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03156228}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776442736587,"responseId":"0631906ff2f098ce49162afde2b1514d"}}
