{"type":"message","id":"1cd334fe","parentId":"ba5c00b5","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:20:40.881Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me verify the config is valid and restart the gateway. Then I'll check what the gateway actually supports for context management, and create a proper solution.Let me also check the session context path and create a session-specific context monitor that runs as a cron.Actually, let me take a different approach. Instead of modifying gateway config, let me:1. Verify the fix worked\n2. Create a cron-based context monitor that compacts the main session\n3. The cron runs `context-monitor` hook regularly\n4. Also create a `compact` session command hookLet me verify config first.","thinkingSignature":"e939fd81c7e7b63fee4897742eaa6a128a6357e20c0cbc51e62ca3f14a5c188c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vauo68jtahsk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/openclaw.mjs config validate 2>&1 | tail -5\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 验证 context 段落 ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint('context:', list(d.get('context', {}).keys()) if 'context' in d else 'NOT IN CONFIG')\nprint('compaction:', d.get('agents',{}).get('defaults',{}).get('compaction',{}))\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":102208,"output":269,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":124115,"cost":{"input":0.0306624,"output":0.0003228,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03228348}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776442836126,"responseId":"063190d1a1f3cc9667f18633a95c4028"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f82a0549","parentId":"1cd334fe","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:20:46.870Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vauo68jtahsk_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Config valid: ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n\n=== 验证 context 段落 ===\ncontext: NOT IN CONFIG\ncompaction: {'mode': 'safeguard'}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":5802,"aggregated":"Config valid: ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n\n=== 验证 context 段落 ===\ncontext: NOT IN CONFIG\ncompaction: {'mode': 'safeguard'}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776442846804}}
{"type":"message","id":"0f335533","parentId":"f82a0549","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:21:07.628Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the config is valid now. But there's no `context` configuration in the gateway config schema. This means the gateway doesn't have a built-in context management configuration.\n\nNow I need to take a different approach. Since the gateway doesn't support `context` config, I need to build context management externally.\n\n**The right architecture**:1. A `context-monitor` cron job that runs every N messages or time interval2. It reads the session context file directly\n3. If over threshold, it generates a summary and writes back a compacted context\n\nThe challenge: **Which session to compact?** The cron job targets `agent:main:main`. \n\nI'll set up a cron that triggers the context-monitor hook, using the session context path to read and compact the session if needed. The HOOK.md declares it listens for `message:preprocessed` events, but since this is a cron job, it'll invoke the handler through the agentTurn payload instead.","thinkingSignature":"ab6361c37f2bbf66662ff1b82da7ba473908d3b5d30dcf4d2075578f083ec9e1"},{"type":"text","text":"配置 schema 不支持 `context` 顶级字段。改用 cron 驱动 + 直接操作 session 文件：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_el3ujdzur60o_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/scripts/context-monitor.js","content":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * Context Monitor - 直接操作 session context 文件\n * 超过阈值时自动压缩\n */\n\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\n\nconst SESSION_PATH = '/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:main/context.json';\nconst MEMORY_DIR = '/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory';\nconst MAX_TOKENS = 140000;        // 140K token 上限\nconst SUMMARIZE_AT = 120000;     // 120K 时触发摘要\nconst PRESERVE_RECENT = 15;      // 保留最近 15 轮\n\nfunction countTokens(text) {\n  if (!text) return 0;\n  const chinese = (text.match(/[\\u4e00-\\u9fa5]/g) || []).length;\n  const other = text.length - chinese;\n  return Math.ceil(chinese / 1.5 + other / 4);\n}\n\nfunction countSessionTokens(messages) {\n  return messages.reduce((sum, m) => {\n    return sum + countTokens(m.content || '') + countTokens(m.name || '') + 20;\n  }, 0);\n}\n\nfunction generateSummary(messages) {\n  const text = messages.map(m => `${m.role}: ${m.content || ''}`).join('\\n');\n  if (text.length < 100) return text;\n  return text.slice(0, 3000) + (text.length > 3000 ? '\\n...[内容已截断]...' : '');\n}\n\nasync function compact(contextPath) {\n  const data = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(contextPath, 'utf8'));\n  const messages = data.messages || [];\n  \n  const systemMsgs = messages.filter(m => m.role === 'system');\n  const recentMsgs = messages.slice(-PRESERVE_RECENT);\n  const oldMessages = messages.slice(0, -PRESERVE_RECENT);\n  \n  if (oldMessages.length === 0) {\n    console.log('[context-monitor] No old messages to compact');\n    return false;\n  }\n  \n  const summaryText = generateSummary(oldMessages);\n  const summaryMsg = {\n    role: 'system',\n    content: `[会话历史摘要 - ${oldMessages.length} 条消息已压缩]: ${summaryText.slice(0, 2000)}`\n  };\n  \n  const compacted = [summaryMsg, ...recentMsgs];\n  \n  data.messages = compacted;\n  fs.writeFileSync(contextPath, JSON.stringify(data, null, 2));\n  \n  console.log(`[context-monitor] 压缩成功: ${messages.length} → ${compacted.length} 条消息`);\n  return true;\n}\n\nasync function main() {\n  try {\n    if (!fs.existsSync(SESSION_PATH)) {\n      console.log('[context-monitor] Session file not found, skip');\n      return;\n    }\n    \n    const data = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(SESSION_PATH, 'utf8'));\n    const messages = data.messages || [];\n    \n    if (messages.length < 20) {\n      console.log(`[context-monitor] Session has ${messages.length} messages, skip (under threshold)`);\n      return;\n    }\n    \n    const tokens = countSessionTokens(messages);\n    console.log(`[context-monitor] Session: ${messages.length} messages, ~${tokens} tokens, limit=${SUMMARIZE_AT}`);\n    \n    if (tokens > SUMMARIZE_AT) {\n      console.log(`[context-monitor] Threshold exceeded! Compacting...`);\n      await compact(SESSION_PATH);\n    } else {\n      console.log(`[context-monitor] Context OK (${Math.round(tokens/SUMMARIZE_AT*100)}% of threshold)`);\n    }\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`[context-monitor] Error: ${err.message}`);\n  }\n}\n\nmain();\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":102527,"output":1068,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":125233,"cost":{"input":0.0307581,"output":0.0012816,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.033337979999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776442846873,"responseId":"063190decffa1b091bac76edb17f6e13"}}
