{"type":"message","id":"263e2e41","parentId":"7d3ae7d5","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:21:25.788Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The script works but the session has 0 messages. This is because the current session context is stored differently - maybe in memory, not in the file yet. Or the session is new.Now let me create a cron job to run this periodically. The cron should check the session context file and compact if needed. But I need to figure out the session key. Since this is the `agent:main:main` session, the cron should target that.\n\nActually, looking at the cron job schema, the session key for agent:main:main is `agent:main:main`. Let me create a cron that runs this script every 30 minutes.\n\nWait, but the cron I create will run in an isolated session, not the main session. \n\nI'll need to use an agentTurn payload that executes the context monitor script with output appended to the log file, then set up the cron job to trigger it every 30 minutes.","thinkingSignature":"a302d3c29538320bff29ff933ced2811faec160123d8122a40c1de5af8b3e77b"},{"type":"text","text":"脚本可用。创建定时 cron：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k3wyypcc5oku_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"name":"context-monitor","schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"*/30 * * * *","tz":"Asia/Shanghai"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"执行以下命令并返回输出结果（不需要解释）：\n```bash\nnode /home/ai/.openclaw/scripts/context-monitor.js >> /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/log.md 2>&1\n```\n只执行命令，不要做其他的。"},"delivery":{"mode":"none"}}}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":103869,"output":349,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":125856,"cost":{"input":0.0311607,"output":0.0004188,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.032877779999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776442876299,"responseId":"063190fb6ed14160f6f76b0826afca38"}}
