{"type":"message","id":"ec39ad38","parentId":"49e0fd4a","timestamp":"2026-04-18T02:51:18.573Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The subagent received the task but it was the literal string \"[AUTO_ROUTE] 帮我写一个 Python 快排\" - it didn't parse the AUTO_ROUTE marker, it just executed the whole thing as the task message. And it actually created a file and wrote Python code to it.\n\nBut the user wanted me to test the AUTO_ROUTE rule from the main agent's SOUL.md. The issue is that when I spawned the subagent, the message included the \"[AUTO_ROUTE]\" prefix literally, and the subagent doesn't have the AUTO_ROUTE rule in its SOUL.md (it's a subagent session).\n\nSo the subagent treated \"[AUTO_ROUTE] 帮我写一个 Python 快排\" as the task itself, created the file. This is NOT the test result we wanted - we wanted the subagent to receive \"帮我写一个 Python 快排\" (without the prefix) and then spawn its OWN sub-sub-agent using the AUTO_ROUTE rule. But that didn't happen because the subagent's SOUL.md doesn't have the AUTO_ROUTE rule.\n \nThe actual behavior was: I spawned a subagent with \"[AUTO_ROUTE] 帮我写一个 Python 快排\" as the message, it received the entire string including the marker, and processed it directly instead of spawning further. The AUTO_ROUTE mechanism requires `/new` to reload the main agent's SOUL.md with the new rule, then when a user sends \"[AUTO_ROUTE]...\" message, the main agent reads it and spawns a subagent—but since the subagent's SOUL.md lacks this rule, it just executes normally.\n\nThe real test should happen after `/new` when the user sends the AUTO_ROUTE message themselves, not through manual spawning.","thinkingSignature":"989bc7f698bc80c67a4282dce4a935039e4a9e78ffaa8cdef290e160635c0f18"},{"type":"text","text":"子 agent 收到了完整字符串 `[AUTO_ROUTE] 帮我写一个 Python 快排`，它没有 AUTO_ROUTE 规则，所以直接执行了（写文件）。\n\n这说明：**当前 session（主 agent）收到 `[AUTO_ROUTE]` 才会触发规则**。\n\n测试需要在 `/new` 之后，由你亲自发一条 `[AUTO_ROUTE]` 开头的消息。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages"