{"type":"message","id":"8da613b4","parentId":"c1eace4f","timestamp":"2026-04-18T02:51:55.769Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I spawned a subagent with the task of sending \"[AUTO_ROUTE] 帮我写一个Python快排\" to the main session. But wait - I need to think about this. The subagent's task is to send that message back to me. But the subagent doesn't have a way to send messages to the parent session - it can only announce results.\n\nActually, the subagent will receive the message \"[AUTO_ROUTE] 帮我写一个Python快排\" as its task. Since the subagent's SOUL.md also has the AUTO_ROUTE rule (because it loads from the workspace), it should trigger sessions_spawn and return NO_REPLY.\n\nWait - does the subagent session load the same SOUL.md? Let me think about this.\n\n\nThe subagent is a fresh session that starts with its own SOUL.md loaded, so it should see the AUTO_ROUTE rule. When it receives \"[AUTO_ROUTE] 帮我写一个Python快排\", the rule should trigger and make it spawn another subagent with the quicksort task, then return NO_REPLY. Let me just wait for the result.","thinkingSignature":"07d41719afb372630ddfe001c709dbff4e7cae9d4767b98bc4febea8724f9846"},{"type":"text","text":"等子 session 完成，看它是否会按 AUTO_ROUTE 规则派发。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":27990,"output":253,"cacheRead":21850,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50093,"cost":{"input":0.008397,"output":0.0003036,"cacheRead":0.0013109999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.010011599999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776480708608,"responseId":"063224c49fb09a35e8fe1dffa715a3c1"}}
