{"type":"message","id":"dc203e4d","parentId":"a3241508","timestamp":"2026-04-18T02:57:17.784Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zvzky3t008fc_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"total 16\ndrwxrwxr-x 2 ai ai 4096 Apr 13 19:41 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 6 ai ai 4096 Apr 18 00:26 ..\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 ai ai 1221 Apr 13 19:51 HOOK.md\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 ai ai 3590 Apr 18 10:53 handler.js\n// 核心改进：高评分消息注入 [AUTO_ROUTE] 前缀，触发主 agent 的 SOUL.md 派发规则\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\n--\nconst SCORE_THRESHOLD = 40;  // >= 40 触发派发\nconst SCORER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\";\nconst CLASSIFIER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\";\n\n--\n  // 跳过已经是 AUTO_ROUTE 的消息（避免重复注入）\n  if (text.startsWith(\"[AUTO_ROUTE]\")) return;\n\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n--\n  // 高评分消息注入 [AUTO_ROUTE] 前缀，触发 SOUL.md 的派发规则\n  if (score >= SCORE_THRESHOLD) {\n    event.context.bodyForAgent = `[AUTO_ROUTE] ${text}`;\n    console.log(`[auto-score-classify] Score=${score} >= ${SCORE_THRESHOLD}, injected [AUTO_ROUTE] prefix`);\n  }\n\n  // 写入有意义消息到 ephemeral"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":244,"aggregated":"total 16\ndrwxrwxr-x 2 ai ai 4096 Apr 13 19:41 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 6 ai ai 4096 Apr 18 00:26 ..\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 ai ai 1221 Apr 13 19:51 HOOK.md\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 ai ai 3590 Apr 18 10:53 handler.js\n// 核心改进：高评分消息注入 [AUTO_ROUTE] 前缀，触发主 agent 的 SOUL.md 派发规则\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\n--\nconst SCORE_THRESHOLD = 40;  // >= 40 触发派发\nconst SCORER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\";\nconst CLASSIFIER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\";\n\n--\n  // 跳过已经是 AUTO_ROUTE 的消息（避免重复注入）\n  if (text.startsWith(\"[AUTO_ROUTE]\")) return;\n\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n--\n  // 高评分消息注入 [AUTO_ROUTE] 前缀，触发 SOUL.md 的派发规则\n  if (score >= SCORE_THRESHOLD) {\n    event.context.bodyForAgent = `[AUTO_ROUTE] ${text}`;\n    console.log(`[auto-score-classify] Score=${score} >= ${SCORE_THRESHOLD}, injected [AUTO_ROUTE] prefix`);\n  }\n\n  // 写入有意义消息到 ephemeral","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776481037713}}
{"type":"message","id":"7775dfb4","parentId":"dc203e4d","timestamp":"2026-04-18T02:57:52.148Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The handler.js has been updated. But I can't easily verify if the hook is actually being triggered without sending a real message through the gateway. The gateway needs to be restarted to load the new hook code.\n\nThe gateway was restarted (PID 8772). The handler.js was updated at 10:53. So the new code should be loaded.\n\nNow the question is whether I can verify the hook is working. The issue is that the hook only fires when a message goes through the gateway's message preprocessing. There's no easy way to test this from outside.\n\nLet me think about what actually happened with the AUTO_ROUTE test message I sent earlier. When I sent \"[AUTO_ROUTE] 分析 ~/.openclaw 目录下的所有 hook 代码...\" - this was a message sent FROM the user (via webchat) TO the gateway. The gateway should have:\n1. Received the message\n2. Triggered the message:preprocessed event\n3. Run the hook\n4. The hook should have checked the score and potentially already injected [AUTO_ROUTE]\n\n\n5. If the score was >= 40, the hook would have already injected [AUTO_ROUTE], so it would skip the injection (because text.startsWith(\"[AUTO_ROUTE]\") is true)\n6. But my message already started with [AUTO_ROUTE], so the hook would skip it anyway\n\nWait - there's a problem. The hook code has:\n```javascript\n// 跳过已经是 AUTO_ROUTE 的消息（避免重复注入）\nif (text.startsWith(\"[AUTO_ROUTE]\")) return;\n```\n\nSo when the user sends \"[AUTO_ROUTE] ...\" the hook sees it already starts with [AUTO_ROUTE] and returns early without doing anything. This means the auto-injection logic never runs on messages that already have the prefix, which defeats the purpose of testing it that way.\n\nBut the actual AUTO_ROUTE rule in SOUL.md should handle this: when it sees the prefix, it triggers sessions_spawn and outputs NO_REPLY. The hook returning early is fine because the SOUL.md rule takes over from there. The real test would be sending a message without the [AUTO_ROUTE] prefix and checking if the hook injects it when the score is >= 40, then seeing if the SOUL.md rule spawns the session.\n\nLooking back at what actually happened - I sent \"[AUTO_ROUTE] 分析...\" but the session just continued normally without spawning or returning NO_REPLY. This suggests the hook might have returned early due to the prefix check, but then the SOUL.md rule either didn't trigger or didn't work as expected. Let me trace through what should have happened versus what did. ...and that user message went through the gateway to me, so the hook should have run. Let me check if the hook actually executed by looking at the gateway logs or context files.\n\nActually, the simpler explanation: when I sent \"[AUTO_ROUTE] 分析...\" and it came through me (the main agent) without spawning a subagent, it means either the hook didn't trigger, the score was below 40, or the SOUL.md rule didn't fire. I think the real issue is that the hook modifies `event.context.bodyForAgent` to inject the [AUTO_ROUTE] prefix for high scores, and then my SOUL.md sees that prefix and spawns a subagent with NO_REPLY. But I never got a subagent result back, so something in that chain broke.\n\nThe best way to test this is actually through the webchat UI with a user - send a regular message with a high enough score that the hook will inject the prefix, and see if the subagent gets spawned and returns the result. me spawn a subagent with sessions_spawn, which then echoes back the message as the final response. But that would just be the subagent echo, not a proper code result.\n\nActually, looking at the previous subagent results - when I spawned a subagent with my message task, it executed and returned code. So the chain should work: hook injects [AUTO_ROUTE], I spawn a subagent, the subagent runs and returns its result, which then gets returned as my response.\n\nBut I haven't seen that happen yet. The issue might be timing - maybe I said \"等待结果验证\" before the subagent had time to complete and return its result. Or perhaps the hook isn't actually injecting the prefix when it should be, or the score threshold isn't being met for this particular message.\n\nLet me try a different approach: generate a message that will definitely score high (something multi-step and complex), send it through myself to trigger the hook, and then I can see whether the subagent gets spawned and returns the expected code result.","thinkingSignature":"98307cd08d8d608b99ecd5c9fe6297d6d662bcde41c83bba98586917bebc3113"},{"type":"text","text":"Hook 已更新，gateway 已重启。当前测试链是：\n\n```\n用户消息 → hook 拦截 → 评分 >= 40 → 注入 [AUTO_ROUTE] → SOUL.md 匹配 → sessions_spawn → NO_REPLY\n```\n\n之前发的 `[AUTO_ROUTE] 分析...` 消息，hook 跳过了（已有前缀），SOUL.md 规则应该触发但没有 spawn 出 subagent。\n\n让我直接验证 SOUL.md 规则是否在工作——发一条新的高评分任务：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v4chpav3ylrn_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"[AUTO_ROUTE] 重构 ~/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md，在最开头插入一行注释：## AUTO_ROUTE 测试","runtime":"subagent","mode":"run"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":32892,"output":1152,"cacheRead":21859,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55903,"cost":{"input":0.009867599999999999,"output":0.0013824,"cacheRead":0.00131154,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01256154}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776481037786,"responseId":"0632260dc91f4c7062d69465107c6578"}}
