{"type":"message","id":"98b27d78","parentId":"6b829a47","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:00:01.745Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to take initiative and test the AUTO_ROUTE chain myself. I should:\n\n1. First check the current SOUL.md to confirm the AUTO_ROUTE rule is there\n2. Then trigger a test - maybe by sending a message to myself that starts with [AUTO_ROUTE] to simulate a user message going through the hook and triggering the rule\n\nBut wait - I need to think about what \"自己干\" means here. The user is telling me to be proactive. But the core issue is: how do I test the hook chain without /new?\n\nThe hook (auto-score-classify) intercepts messages BEFORE the agent processes them. I can't intercept my own message to the gateway and inject the [AUTO_ROUTE] prefix.\n\n\nI'm considering whether I can use the Gateway API directly to send a message that mimics a user message, which would trigger the hook and go through the full chain including the AUTO_ROUTE rule. The most practical approach is to first verify the SOUL.md has the AUTO_ROUTE rule at the top, then use the Gateway API to send a test message with [AUTO_ROUTE] and see if it spawns a sub-agent and returns NO_REPLY.","thinkingSignature":"24fe330dd24b55fadf3d576802036def71f7dbcd947ce0117d8428ce7adf9460"},{"type":"text","text":"### 思考\n\n当前障碍：\n- AUTO_ROUTE 规则需要 `/new` 才能生效（SOUL.md 在 session 启动时加载）\n- 无法在当前 session 触发 hook 对我自己的消息做注入\n- 子 agent 独立 session，不继承主 SOUL.md\n\n**可行的主动测试**：通过 Gateway API 直接发消息，模拟用户发消息给主 session，看 hook 是否注入前缀。\n\n先确认 SOUL.md 头部内容，然后调用 Gateway API 触发：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yljn98g3d1tb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -15 ~/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58,"output":381,"cacheRead":54989,"cacheWrite":736,"totalTokens":56164,"cost":{"input":0.0000174,"output":0.0004572,"cacheRead":0.0032993399999999996,"cache