{"type":"message","id":"a34298d5","parentId":"2b8e00f3","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:01:07.192Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The sessions_send timed out because it waited for the agent to respond. But the agent should have received the message, triggered the AUTO_ROUTE rule, spawned a subagent, and returned NO_REPLY. But sessions_send timed out waiting for a response.\n\nThis could mean:\n1. The agent received the message, triggered AUTO_ROUTE, spawned a subagent, returned NO_REPLY\n2. But the NO_REPLY might not have satisfied sessions_send's wait for a response\n\nActually the issue is that sessions_send waits for the agent's response. The agent would have output NO_REPLY, which might not be considered a \"response\" by sessions_send, causing a timeout.\n\nActually wait - sessions_send timed out. \n\nSo the agent likely did process the message and spawn a subagent, but NO_REPLY doesn't count as a meaningful response that sessions_send can return back to me. The subagent is running independently though, so the question is whether it actually received the routed message and will produce results. I should just wait for the subagent completion notification instead of trying to force sessions_send to get something back.","thinkingSignature":"a2fbb9c05e2f8b2abc191a2e566c3e49a537bdb8507d3572ed88060a1d410165"},{"type":"text","text":"sessions_send 超时了——这可能意味着 agent 收到了消息，触发了 AUTO_ROUTE 规则，spawn 了 subagent，然后输出了 NO_REPLY（sessions_send 拿不到回复所以超时）。\n\n子 agent 在跑。等待完成通知。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35640,"output":280,"cacheRead":21859,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57779,"cost":{"input":0.010692,"output":0.000336,"cacheRead":0.00131154,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01233954}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776481258537,"responseId":"063226e9505aec8aaa0ed87927acd20b"}}
