{"type":"message","id":"3697c431","parentId":"2da0aeac","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:09:17.287Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to be 100% sure the hook injection works. Let me think about how to actually verify this.\n\nThe key question: when a real user message goes through the gateway to the hook, does the hook's modification of `event.context.bodyForAgent` actually affect what the agent receives?\n\nThe only way to test this is:\n1. Have the gateway receive a real message\n2. Check what the hook writes/modifies\n\nSince I can't directly intercept the hook's execution, I need to think of an indirect test.\n\nOne approach: have the hook write to a known file when it injects the prefix. Then I can check that file.\n\nAnother approach: since the hook runs synchronously before the agent, if I send a message that would score >= 40, and the hook successfully injects the prefix, the agent would receive the prefixed message and trigger AUTO_ROUTE. If the hook doesn't inject, the agent receives the normal message.\n\nSo the test is:\n1. Send a high-scoring task via sessions_send to the main session\n2. Check if a subagent gets spawned (which we would see as a subagent_announce event)\n3. If no subagent spawns, the hook injection didn't work\n\nActually, we already tried this! sessions_send to agent:main:main with [AUTO_ROUTE] message worked - subagent got spawned. But that was because WE sent the [AUTO_ROUTE] prefix manually, not because the hook injected it.\n\nTo test the hook properly, I need to:\n1. Send a high-scoring message WITHOUT [AUTO_ROUTE] prefix\n2. See if the hook injects the prefix and a subagent gets spawned\n\nBut here's the problem: sessions_send delivers to the agent which then processes. The hook runs in the gateway's pre-processing stage. When I use sessions_send, does the gateway run the hook?\n\n\nActually, I think sessions_send bypasses the hook entirely - it delivers directly to the agent. So I need the real gateway endpoint that processes incoming messages through the hook. Let me check the gateway's HTTP API to POST a message directly and see if the hook actually runs. The hook logs to stdout/stderr which should go to the gateway process logs, so I could check those after making the request.\n\nActually, I should just write a test hook that directly modifies event.context.bodyForAgent to prepend [AUTO_ROUTE], restart the gateway, send a high-scoring message, and see if a subagent spawns. If the hook successfully injects the prefix, the AUTO_ROUTE rule triggers and spawns a subagent - that would confirm the approach works.","thinkingSignature":"56ed92aeee37a057bf9b6d5e2fdea4583a93c15ca712ed4474f2c0ddd14b877e"},{"type":"text","text":"好，彻底验证 hook 注入。我来写一个能确认 bodyForAgent 是否被修改的测试：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cku98buws7nv_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js","content":"// auto-score-classify hook v4 - 带验证日志\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nconst SCORE_THRESHOLD = 40;\nconst SCORER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\";\nconst CLASSIFIER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\";\nconst HOOK_LOG = \"/tmp/auto-score-classify-hook.log\";\n\nfunction log(...args) {\n  const msg = `[${new Date().toISOString()}] ${args.join(\" \")}`;\n  console.log(msg);\n  fs.appendFileSync(HOOK_LOG, msg + \"\\n\");\n}\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 4000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      { method: \"POST\", headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) } },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => { try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); } catch { resolve(null); } });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(SCORER_URL, { prompt }, 4000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") return;\n\n  const text = event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\";\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) return;\n\n  // 跳过已经是 AUTO_ROUTE 的消息\n  if (text.startsWith(\"[AUTO_ROUTE]\")) {\n    log(\"SKIP: already has [AUTO_ROUTE] prefix\");\n    return;\n  }\n\n  log(`ORIGINAL TEXT: \"${text.slice(0, 100)}\"`);\n\n  const scoringResult = await Promise.race([\n    runScoring(text),\n    new Promise(r => setTimeout(() => r(null), 3000)),\n  ]);\n\n  const scoring = scoringResult;\n  const score = scoring?.score ?? 0;\n\n  log(`SCORE: ${score} (threshold=${SCORE_THRESHOLD})`);\n\n  if (score >= SCORE_THRESHOLD) {\n    const originalText = text;\n    event.context.bodyForAgent = `[AUTO_ROUTE] ${text}`;\n    log(`INJECTED: \"[AUTO_ROUTE] ${originalText.slice(0, 80)}...\"`);\n    log(`MODIFIED bodyForAgent: \"${event.context.bodyForAgent.slice(0, 100)}\"`);\n  } else {\n    log(`NO INJECTION: score ${score} < ${SCORE_THRESHOLD}`);\n  }\n\n  // 写 context.json\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n  ensureDir(sessionDir);\n  try {\n    fs.writeFileSync(path.join(sessionDir, \"context.json\"), JSON.stringify({ scoring, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() }, null, 2));\n  } catch {}\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58,"output":1382,"cacheRead":58297,"cacheWrite":92,"totalTokens":59829,"cost":{"input":0.0000174,"output":0.0016584,"cacheRead":0.0034978199999999996,"cacheWrite":0.0000345,"total":0.005208119999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776481724888,"responseId":"063228bca7e319f38e0258a391ff08c0"}}
