{"type":"message","id":"3461e960","parentId":"16cce446","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:12:44.621Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No output - the hook log is empty. Either:1. The hook didn't run at all (event didn't match `message:preprocessed`)\n2. The log file path is wrong\n3. The hook errored before writing to log\n\nLet me check if the hook is even firing. The issue is that the hook's `handler.js` file was updated, but the gateway is using the `auto-score-classify` plugin (from openclaw.json plugins.entries). Let me check how the hook is registered and whether it's using the handler.js file.\n\nActually, let me look at the hook registration more carefully. The hook is at `~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js`. But how is it loaded? Let me check the openclaw.json.","thinkingSignature":"0a5a525fbdbc2661307c6826824b27b2831281151a078278f9f548070f248617"},{"type":"text","text":"Hook 日志是空的，说明 hook 可能根本没运行。先确认 hook 是如何加载的：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_423vqjo7rsxv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); hooks=d.get('hooks',{}); entries=d.get('plugins',{}).get('entries',{}); print('hooks:', json.dumps(hooks, indent=2)); print('plugin entries:', list(entries.keys()))\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":38172,"output":277,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60314,"cost":{"input":0.0114516,"output":0.0003324,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.013095899999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776481958121,"responseId":"063229a41a6c7d260ff5caae19e557fc"}}
