{"type":"message","id":"b8c432b9","parentId":"4938f8cf","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:13:31.229Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The hook is at `~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js`. For it to be loaded by the gateway via `hooks.internal.entries`, I need to check how the gateway resolves the path. Looking at other entries in `hooks.internal.entries`, they don't have a `path` field - they're just named hooks that the gateway knows how to load internally.\n\nBut `auto-score-classify` is not a built-in hook - it's a custom hook. So I need to either:\n1. Register it with a `path` field (if the gateway supports this for custom hooks)\n2. Or find another way to load it\n\nLet me check how the `context_hook` (which IS in `hooks.internal.entries`) is loaded. It might be a built-in. Let me check if there's an extensions directory with auto-score-classify.\n\n\nActually, I'm seeing two separate system designs here - the internal hooks system in `hooks.internal.entries` with built-in hooks like `session-memory` and `command-logger`, versus a plugin system in `plugins.entries` that includes things like feishu, memory-lancedb, and active-memory. The `auto-score-classify` hook is currently mispositioned in `plugins.entries` when it should be registered in the hooks system instead.\n\nLet me look at what the context-hook.js file contains to understand how custom hooks are supposed to be loaded and where `auto-score-classify` should actually be registered.","thinkingSignature":"e07aa0f27f55baa95819c563537fc593b52eb9ae7d10a539e5f55d3f95fe9a84"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bknu71ubrokj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -5 ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41502,"output":338,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63705,"cost":{"input":0.0124506,"output":0.0004056,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0