{"type":"message","id":"a0fa37c1","parentId":"723c2510","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:13:43.584Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a different format. Let me check the gateway's hook loading mechanism. The key question is: does the gateway support loading hooks from a `path` in `hooks.internal.entries`?\n\nActually, looking at the openclaw extension system - the hooks in `~/.openclaw/hooks/` seem to be legacy or manually-loaded hooks, not the ones registered in `hooks.internal.entries`. The gateway's internal hook system (`hooks.internal.entries`) likely loads built-in hooks only.\n\nThe `auto-score-classify` plugin was previously set up as a `plugins.entry` but it never worked because it was the wrong system.\n\nWait - let me check if there's a `plugins` directory with auto-score-classify:","thinkingSignature":"005beb7bdce4f7d2d123251c5e21654543a3512d441a94fa432024f55515ffc3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oqv8pr2cgoal_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw/extensions -name \"*.js\" -path \"*auto-score*\" 2>/dev/null\n# Check if auto-score-classify was loaded as a plugin\nfind ~/.openclaw -name \"package.json\" -path \"*auto-score*\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42034,"output":226,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64125,"cost":{"input":0.0126102,"output":0.0002712,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014193299999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776482015745,"responseId":"063229de9b7299aa1f1a0952889d8c20"}}
