{"type":"message","id":"cd4d3d6e","parentId":"1ec640b7","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:13:52.719Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No plugin found. Let me look at how the gateway loads hooks from `hooks.internal.entries` to understand what format the hook file should be in.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach. Instead of fighting the hook registration system, let me check if the existing `context-hook.js` (which IS in `hooks.internal.entries`) actually works. If it does, then maybe the hook system DOES support custom hooks via a path.\n\nBut wait - the `context_hook` in `hooks.internal.entries` doesn't have a path. It's just `\"context_hook\": {\"enabled\": true}`. So the gateway must be loading it from a built-in location.\n\nLet me look at the gateway's dist to find how it loads hooks:","thinkingSignature":"f61d2eacc0f9a29fa06e8f0e98efffdde44a87720456ba6023ba88f4427a427b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kegt8bytkd22_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"hooks.internal\\|auto-score-classify\\|handler\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/gateway/ 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"hook\\|auto-score\" | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42278,"output":225,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64368,"cost":{"input":0.0126834,"output":0.00027,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014265299999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776482024243,"responseId":"063229e8f6b61f50dfefde0a2afc7e84"}}
