{"type":"message","id":"d2fa9f27","parentId":"cd29b920","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:14:05.977Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see it clearly:\n\n1. `fireAndForgetHook(triggerInternalHook(createInternalHookEvent(\"message\", \"preprocessed\", ...)))` - this is what fires the `message:preprocessed` hook\n2. Hooks are loaded from \"managed or workspace hook directory with HOOK.md + handler.js\"\n3. The config key is `hooks.internal.entries.<hookKey>` with a path\n\nSo the gateway DOES support custom hooks via path in `hooks.internal.entries`. The format is:\n```json\n\"auto-score-classify\": {\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"path\": \"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js\"\n\n\n}\n```\n\nI found the hook registration in `openclaw.json` and confirmed it's pointing to the right handler file. The real problem is that after adding the registration, the gateway isn't picking it up. The `context_hook` entry has no path property because it's built-in, but `auto-score-classify` needs that path specified to be found. Let me check the actual hook loading mechanism in the internal hooks file to see what's happening.","thinkingSignature":"1d80ee1ff29261fadd2acd9308bf90195eb848a10d962388e923b0fa9a7827bb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6pb7d4fsj5on_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A5 \"hooks.internal.load.extraDirs\\|extraDirs\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/runtime-schema-BpoRdXIq.js | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43518,"output":298,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65681,"cost":{"input":0.0130554,"output":0.00035759999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014724899999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776482038357,"responseId":"063229f507e5845db99c1a821cf529cf"}}
