{"type":"message","id":"92df529d","parentId":"47aba643","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:14:24.253Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - internal hooks are registered via `registerInternalHook()` which is called by plugins or built-in components. The `hooks.internal.entries` config just enables/disables them, but the actual hook CODE needs to be registered through a plugin or the gateway's internal system.\n\nSo `auto-score-classify` needs to be a plugin that registers the hook via `registerInternalHook('message:preprocessed', handler)`. Just having a handler.js file in the hooks directory isn't enough.\n\nLet me check how the `context-hook.js` works and whether it's a plugin that registers hooks:","thinkingSignature":"9fd77ab479ebf51f55cd20c7c842fdbbd33e2bef5783526631fd065086fe2130"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ama3026jqdm8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"registerInternalHook\\|message:preprocessed\\|exports\\|module\" ~/.openclaw/hooks/context-hook.js | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":44846,"output":172,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66883,"cost":{"input":0.0134538,"output":0.0002064,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0149721}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776482058179,"responseId":"06322a09679b11d66f4a2d591c5a8d74"}}
