{"type":"message","id":"d816308c","parentId":"e8966619","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:14:30.955Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `context-hook.js` exports a `handler` function via CommonJS `module.exports`. The file doesn't call `registerInternalHook` directly - that must be done by the gateway when loading the hook.\n\nLet me look at how the gateway actually loads hooks from the hooks directory. Maybe there's a loader that reads `handler.js` files from specific directories.\n\nActually, looking at the `openclaw-listener` - it's a separate process that might handle hooks. Let me check.","thinkingSignature":"6e72f2dc4961ba01e551fe2b09dcf1e9ae3b9ea547450412c0ea1dab91d3c39a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2x5qed8ln8u8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"hooks.*handler\\|handler.*path\\|load.*hook\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/listener/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":45048,"output":168,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67081,"cost":{"input":0.0135144,"output":0.0002016,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.015027899999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776482064700,"responseId":"06322a0ff18a6684c436d35ff459a15d"}}
