{"type":"message","id":"a1ce2882","parentId":"1e34da1c","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:14:47.944Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So there's no `auto-score-classify` plugin. It was never actually deployed as a plugin. The hook code I wrote was at `~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js` but was never actually loaded because it wasn't registered.\n\nNow I need to understand: HOW does the gateway load hooks from `~/.openclaw/hooks/`? Is there a convention where it looks in that directory?\n\nLet me check the gateway's source code for how it loads hooks from the hooks directory:","thinkingSignature":"6556641845aa4f083e94d1f632da73920ee3aa030d72b6486f4176e3d45fb9a2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_usgmbotbf8vt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"hooks/\\|/hooks\\|hooksDir\\|hookDir\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".js.map\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":45595,"output":179,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67639,"cost":{"input":0.0136785,"output":0.0002148,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.015205199999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776482080940,"responseId":"06322a20764527fb12e23700c967d65d"}}
