{"type":"message","id":"da5b3ed2","parentId":"98b94119","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:15:33.555Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! The `openclaw-listener` has a `MessageHandler` that uses `v8Client` to call the 3104 classifier and 3103 scorer! The `auto-score-classify` logic is in the `openclaw-listener`, not in a hook loaded by the gateway!\n\nThe `openclaw-listener` is a separate service that intercepts messages, calls the v8 classifier/scorer, and then forwards to the gateway. The hook I wrote at `~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js` is a ghost that was never used!\n\nLet me verify this by looking at the v8Client:","thinkingSignature":"220aa285816551099bb007f4d3ca4bc1437ba8ea627e8ff041df704fcefc6364"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h08je47op3u9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/ai/openclaw-listener/dist/clients/v8Client.js 2>/dev/null | head -60"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48580,"output":184,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70629,"cost":{"input":0.014574,"output":0.0002208,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0161067}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776482129231,"responseId":"06322a4f3cc963623aec71529ff80715"}}
