{"type":"message","id":"56b6d64b","parentId":"90368b75","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:15:53.996Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the ENTIRE picture:\n\n1. The `openclaw-listener` is a message proxy that:\n   - Receives messages\n   - Calls v8 classifier (3104) and scorer (3103)\n   - Logs the results\n   - FORWARDS to the gateway (via `gatewayClient.send`)\n\n2. The `messageHandler` does classification and scoring, but:\n   - It logs the results\n   - It sends a reply via `gatewayClient.send({ type: 'reply', content: reply })`\n   - But it doesn't modify the message that goes to the gateway!\n\n3. The gateway receives the message through the listener's gatewayClient.send(), which just sends the raw message without the classification or scoring context attached.\n\n4. So the hook I wrote at `~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js` was never even being called—the real classification was happening in the listener's `messageHandler.js` before the gateway ever saw the message.\n\nThe listener was doing all the v8 classification work but throwing away the results, while I was writing a gateway hook that never actually ran. The actual flow should be: listener classifies and scores, then injects those results into the message context that the gateway receives, but currently that context just gets logged and forgotten.","thinkingSignature":"35e2f6864bf15b2ebca0faf6834c90e56e452782feedf8f10fe051303b691d2b"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了！**真正在做分类评分的是 `openclaw-listener`**，不是 gateway hook。\n\n`openclaw-listener/dist/messageHandler.js` 调用 3104+3103，但结果只是**写日志**，没有注入到发给 gateway 的消息里。\n\n这就是为什么 hook 一直没生效——它根本不在 gateway 的消息处理流程里。\n\n**真正需要改的是 `openclaw-listener`**。让我看它是怎么发消息给 gateway 的：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mosr0cpteliz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/ai/openclaw-listener/dist/gatewayClient.js 2>/dev/null | head -80"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2