{"type":"message","id":"718f03c2","parentId":"283a61d1","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:16:45.254Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try a different approach. Since we know the gateway fires `message:preprocessed` internally (from the earlier grep), the hook registration must work somehow. Let me look at the actual hook registration mechanism.\n\nActually, I think I've been overcomplicating this. Let me go back to the simplest question: **was the auto-score-classify hook ever actually working?**\n\nThe hook at `~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js` was written by me, but it was never registered anywhere that the gateway actually reads from. The `hooks.internal.entries` config doesn't have `auto-score-classify` until I just added it now.\n \nThe real classification and scoring were actually happening in the `openclaw-listener` process all along—that's what was logging those analysis results. Now I need to modify the `gatewayClient.send()` method to include the classification and scoring data in the WebSocket message it sends to the gateway, so that information gets passed through to the hook.\n\nBut wait, I'm realizing the gateway is receiving messages directly from the Feishu channel, not through the listener. The listener is connected via WebSocket and receives those same messages, processes them through the v8 classifier, but then the gateway never sees those classification results. I could make the listener send those results back to the gateway as a separate message, but the gateway has no way to correlate them with the original message it already received.\n\nLet me reconsider the flow from the beginning. When a user sends a message to the Feishu channel, it goes to the gateway, which creates a session and fires the `message:preprocessed` hook before the agent processes it. The gateway also forwards that same message to the listener via WebSocket, which runs classification and scoring, then sends back a reply message. The gateway then forwards that reply to the Feishu channel as the bot's response.\n\nBut I'm not seeing where the listener's reply actually gets used as the bot's response—the gateway seems to generate its own response through the agent instead. I need to trace through the actual gateway code to understand how it handles the reply coming back from the listener.","thinkingSignature":"d157cf9cffdd30d582d4f03ab76085999cd38cf52c9b3d5a3b4d55e93f212704"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8rfq4t0gjlh4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"reply.*type\\|type.*reply\\|gatewayClient\\|Listener\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/gateway-B1XKgomf.js 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":53636,"output":514,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76015,"cost":{"input":0.0160908,"output":0.0006167999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0180195}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776482187656,"responseId":"06322a8b5ef707c927f127fce2ad4367"}}
