{"type":"message","id":"f4b0bd57","parentId":"78a70870","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:17:15.855Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `auto-score-classify` appears in `postinstall-inventory.json` (which lists all files installed) and `prompt-select-styled-rf05yZzB.js` (which mentions hooks in a help text). It doesn't appear as loaded code.\n\nSo my hook was never loaded. The classification/scoring was happening in the `openclaw-listener`.\n\nNow I understand the ENTIRE picture. Let me explain it to the user and then decide what to do:\n\n**Current architecture:**\n1. Messages from Feishu → Gateway → Agent\n2. Gateway also forwards to openclaw-listener via WebSocket\n3. openclaw-listener does classification/scoring → sends reply back to gateway\n4. The gateway's `reply` from listener is sent back to the Feishu channel\n\n\n5. But the gateway's own agent is also generating responses to the same messages, so the listener's reply and the agent's reply are both being sent back to Feishu—creating duplicate responses.\n\nLooking at the gateway code, when the listener sends `{ type: 'reply', content: reply }`, the gateway treats that as a message to forward to the channel. But I'm not certain how the gateway differentiates between the agent's response and the listener's reply, or if they're being sent independently.\n\nThe real issue is that my hook was never actually loaded by the gateway because it wasn't registered. The `auto-score-classify` hook file I created was dead code—the classification and scoring was actually happening in the `openclaw-listener`. So I need to either register the hook properly in `hooks.internal.entries` if the gateway supports that, or modify the `openclaw-listener` to inject the `[AUTO_ROUTE]` prefix when scores meet the threshold.\n\nLet me check the config I added to see if the path-based registration is even valid, since I'm not sure the gateway actually supports that approach.","thinkingSignature":"3f642b83d543eabccc8f22a6da5a4e766092a78e39d0a0be7c81710ec2e69525"},{"type":"text","text":"现在完全清楚了：\n\n**`openclaw-listener` 才是真正在做分类评分的地方**，不是 gateway hook。\n\nGateway hook 我写的 `handler.js` 从未被加载过——它根本不在 gateway 的 hook 系统里。\n\n需要把 hook 注册加入 `hooks.internal.entries`。但关键问题是——注册后 gateway 从哪加载 hook 代码？\n\n让我检查 gateway 怎么找 hook 实现：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l29mxxxpwtfx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A10 \"auto-score-classify\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/postinstall-inventory.json | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54634,"output":526,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77025,"cost":{"input":0.0163902,"output":0.0006312,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0183333}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776482216981,"responseId":"06322aa8d773532cfd571ed0ca50886d"}}
