{"type":"message","id":"b5320c88","parentId":"ea6bdc72","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:17:53.193Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try a completely different approach. Instead of trying to figure out how hooks are loaded, let me just look at whether the gateway's internal hook registry (`registerInternalHook`) is populated from the config file. If so, then adding `auto-score-classify` to `hooks.internal.entries` with the right path should work.\n\nActually, looking at the issue from a different angle: maybe `auto-score-classify` was NEVER supposed to be a gateway hook. Maybe it was always intended to be a plugin in the `openclaw-listener` system. The `openclaw-listener` already does classification and scoring - so the \"hook\" was always supposed to be in the listener, not the gateway.\n\nIn that case, what I need to do is:\n1. Modify the `openclaw-listener` to inject `[AUTO_ROUTE]` prefix when score >= 40\n\n\n2. The gateway receives the modified message and the agent's SOUL.md triggers\n\nBut wait - the listener sends `{ type: 'reply' }` to the gateway, not a message that goes to the agent. So the flow would be: listener classifies → if score >= 40, injects [AUTO_ROUTE] into the reply → gateway sends reply to Feishu channel. That would just send \"[AUTO_ROUTE] 帮我写个快排\" back to the user, which isn't what we want. We need the gateway to receive a message with the [AUTO_ROUTE] prefix so the agent can process it.\n\nActually, I think I've been misunderstanding the architecture. The Feishu channel is bound in `openclaw.json` to `agentId: \"main\"`, which means messages go directly to the gateway and then to the main agent - the listener isn't in the critical path at all. The listener only receives messages forwarded by the gateway and sends back replies, but those replies don't go back to the agent, they go back to the Feishu channel. So the listener is more of a passive monitor that classifies messages for logging purposes rather than something that intercepts and modifies the message flow to the agent.\n\nLet me look at the gateway code to see if there's actually a `message:preprocessed` hook firing that I've been missing.","thinkingSignature":"53a8fb736c20f786c9018ed3e9079037c9bb4a50ab3733fd94d40eb9f680ae22"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ssaumhubceth_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"message:preprocessed\\|preprocessed\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/get-reply-XW5nFnK2.js 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":55929,"output":534,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78328,"cost":{"input":0.0167787,"output":0.0006408,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.018731400000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776482258846,"responseId":"06322ad1052a6785b7a3622142d180d8"}}
