{"type":"message","id":"c63eaa47","parentId":"4ba8aaa9","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:24:53.918Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The workspace hooks directory doesn't exist at `~/.openclaw/workspace/hooks/`. But wait - the workspace is `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace`. Let me check if there's a hooks directory there.\n\nActually, `ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/` returned \"NOT EXISTS\" for `hooks/` - so `~/.openclaw/workspace/hooks/` doesn't exist. This means gateway can't find the hook through workspace discovery.\n\nBut I also added `\"path\": \"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js\"` to the `hooks.internal.entries.auto-score-classify` config entry. \n\nHowever, looking at the legacy handler loading code, it validates that the module path must be workspace-relative, not absolute - so an absolute path like `/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/...` would fail that validation check.\n\nThis means both the workspace discovery approach (hooks dir doesn't exist) and the absolute path approach (rejected by security check) won't work. I need to create `~/.openclaw/workspace/hooks/` and move the hook there instead.","thinkingSignature":"09b2642ea5ee160cdb58e38fd63272afba81c3bdec835a71043221b4ff2038ff"},{"type":"text","text":"Workspace hooks 目录不存在。Gateway 只会扫描 workspace 内的 hooks 目录。\n\n**解决方案**：在 workspace 下创建 hooks 目录并软链接：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_98md3myohueg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p ~/.openclaw/workspace/hooks\nln -sf /home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify ~/.openclaw/workspace/hooks/auto-score-classify\nls ~/.openclaw/workspace/hooks/"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":55869,"output":329,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78063,"cost":{"input":0.0167607,"output":0.0003948,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.018467400000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776482684446,"responseId":"06322c7b982dd7a