{"type":"message","id":"aa1c7dca","parentId":"772485ed","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:25:04.726Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but the config I added to `hooks.internal.entries` has `\"path\": \"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js\"`. This path is absolute, which won't work for legacy hook loading.\n\nLet me re-think:\n1. Directory-based hook discovery: scans `~/.openclaw/workspace/hooks/` → finds `auto-score-classify/` → reads `HOOK.md` → loads handler\n2. Legacy hook loading: requires workspace-relative path (not absolute)\n\nFor the directory-based discovery to work, the hook needs to be in `~/.openclaw/workspace/hooks/auto-score-classify/` with a `HOOK.md` file. I've now created a symlink there. But wait - the `HOOK.md` in the actual hook directory should be there already since I can see it in `ls ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/`.\n\n\nLet me check if the symlink was created correctly and if the `HOOK.md` file is actually present in the linked directory.","thinkingSignature":"aefbbc8bb992a56cdcb70d95e8cbfadcbe0dd5d6b095d0e26e2b4aa4b2759214"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p0z2fnq7gg71_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/hooks/auto-score-classify/\ncat ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/HOOK.md 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":56218,"output":279,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78362,"cost":{"input":0.0168654,"output":0.0003348,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0185121}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776482694383,"responseId":"06322c86b28b3d400d12c825d2a66fab"}}
