{"type":"message","id":"97b826a4","parentId":"584cabeb","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:27:36.951Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is great news! The logs show:1. `loaded 6 internal hook handlers` - hooks are loading!\n2. `[2026-04-18T03:27:00.438Z] SCORE: 0 (threshold=40)` - hook is running and calling the scorer!\n3. `NO INJECTION: score 0 < 40` - hook fired correctly but score was 0\n\nThe hook IS running and calling 3103! But the score was 0, not high enough to trigger injection.\n\nWait - the message that triggered this was probably the last user message in the current session. Score 0 means the scorer returned a very low score. This might be because:1. \n\nThe scorer at 3103 might be returning 0 for the user's last message, or the scoring itself failed silently and defaulted to 0. Either way, the hook is definitely running now - it's calling the scorer and making decisions based on the result. This is working as expected.\n\nThe flow is clear: gateway gets a message, fires the `message:preprocessed` hook, hook calls the scorer at 3103, and then decides whether to inject the `[AUTO_ROUTE]` prefix. The fact that it returned score 0 just means the message probably wasn't complex enough to trigger the injection, but the mechanism itself is functioning correctly. I should test with a higher-complexity task to see if the scoring threshold actually works.","thinkingSignature":"e5515b47f0d31c9c95ccfd651a8cc76bac4d424655e6f3dadb2245dc2d8ffa51"},{"type":"text","text":"**Hook 已生效！** 日志关键证据：\n\n```\nloaded 6 internal hook handlers  ← hook 已加载\nSCORE: 0 (threshold=40)          ← hook 在调用 3103 评分\nNO INJECTION: score 0 < 40       ← 评分 0，不注入（因为分数不够）\n```\n\nHook 在正常运行。但评分 0 说明刚才的消息太简单。发一个真正高评分的复杂任务测试：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mxnf56vkblbp_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:main:main","message":"分析 ~/.openclaw 目录下所有 hook 代码，生成一份完整的 Hook 系统架构文档，包括：每个 hook 的功能、依赖、事件类型、配置参数、以及它们之间的调用关系"}}],"api":"