{"type":"message","id":"1a318a4d","parentId":"c8cc2556","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:36:41.002Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to use my initiative to fully get the system running. Let me think about the three problems and how to fix them:\n\n1. **Hook loading path**: Need to create symlinks in `~/.openclaw/workspace/hooks/` pointing to `~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify` - already done ✅\n\n2. **3103 scorer service**: Need to create an HTTP server that wraps `scoring.js` and listens on port 3103. This is the critical missing piece.\n\n3. **Hook injection + SOUL.md chain**: Already fixed - AUTO_ROUTE rule in SOUL.md, hook injects prefix.\n\nThe main remaining blocker is #2. I need to:\n- Write a simple HTTP server that wraps `scoring.js`\n- Make it run on port 3103\n- Register it as a systemd service or background process\n- Verify it works\n\nLet me think about how to do this properly.\n\nThe v8/src/scoring/scoring.js exports `scoreTask(prompt, context)`. I need to wrap it with an HTTP server.\n\nLet me also think about what \"全面跑通\" means:\n1. Hook loads and runs ✅ (just verified)\n2. 3105 classifier works (already confirmed running on 3105)\n3. 3103 scorer works (needs to be started)\n4. Hook injection works (needs testing with a real high-scoring message)\n5. SOUL.md AUTO_ROUTE rule works (verified through sessions_send)\n6. sessions_spawn works (verified)\n7. subagent results return to user (verified through subagent_announce)\n\nSo the only remaining critical piece is #3 - starting the 3103 scorer service.\n\n\nFor the HTTP server, I'll use Express since it's already in the v8 project dependencies, or fall back to Node's built-in http module to keep dependencies minimal. I'll write a simple wrapper around `scoring.js` that exposes the `scoreTask` function as an HTTP endpoint.\n\nThe tricky part is that the hook sends requests with a `prompt` field, but the scoring function expects that field in the request body. I need to check the adapter implementation to see how it transforms the incoming request format.\n\nLooking at the adapter code, it extracts text from the request body using `body.prompt || body.text || body.messages`, so either format should work. Now I can write the HTTP server wrapper.\n\nBeyond that, there's also the issue of clearing out legacy hooks that reference non-existent services like the context_hook.js and on-message.sh scripts.\n\nI should prioritize the core blockers: getting the 3103 HTTP server running first, then handling the cleanup work.","thinkingSignature":"e08b0981dc02deeaba080516dc0e0b9baf3f53aa961bd7977ea5a969d7408713"},{"type":"text","text":"\n### 思考\n\n**核心问题**：3103 scorer 服务不存在，hook 永远拿不到评分。\n\n**修复路径**：\n1. 写一个 HTTP 服务器包装 `scoring.js`，监听 3103\n2. 写成 systemd 服务，开机自启\n3. 清理 legacy hooks（context-hook.js 等已无对应服务）\n\n先解决 3103 scorer——这是最短板。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ogsuuayesf5g_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scripts/scorer-server.js","content":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * v8 Scoring HTTP Server\n * Wraps scoring.js as an HTTP API on port 3103\n */\n\nconst http = require('http');\nconst scoring = require('../src/scoring/scoring');\n\nconst PORT = process.env.PORT || 3103;\nconst HOST = process.env.HOST || '0.0.0.0';\n\nfunction parseBody(req) {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    let body = '';\n    req.on('data', chunk => (body += chunk));\n    req.on('end', () => {\n      try { resolve(body ? JSON.parse(body) : {}); }\n      catch { reject(new Error('Invalid JSON')); }\n    });\n    req.on('error', reject);\n  });\n}\n\nconst server = http.createServer(async (req, res) => {\n  // CORS\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'POST, OPTIONS');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type');\n\n  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') {\n    res.writeHead(204);\n    res.end();\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const url = new URL(req.url, `http://${req.headers.host}`);\n\n  // Health check\n  if (url.pathname === '/health' || url.pathname === '/') {\n    res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n    res.end(JSON.stringify({ status: 'ok', service: 'v8-scorer', port: PORT }));\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Score endpoint\n  if (req.method === 'POST' && (url.pathname === '/api/score' || url.pathname === '/score')) {\n    try {\n      const body = await parseBody(req);\n      const prompt = body.prompt || body.text || body.messages?.[0]?.text || '';\n      const context = body.context || {};\n\n      const result = scoring.scoreTask(prompt, context);\n\n      res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n      res.end(JSON.stringify(result));\n    } catch (err) {\n      console.error('[scorer] Error:', err.message);\n      res.writeHead(500, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n      res.end(JSON.stringify({ error: err.message }));\n    }\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Not found\n  res.writeHead(404, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n  res.end(JSON.stringify({ error: 'Not found' }));\n});\n\nserver.listen(PORT, HOST, () => {\n  console.log(`[scorer] v8 scoring server running on http://${HOST}:${PORT}`);\n  console.log(`[scorer] Endpoint: POST /api/score { prompt: \"...\" }`);\n});\n\n// Graceful shutdown\nprocess.on('SIGTERM', () => {\n  console.log('[scorer] SIGTERM, shutting down');\n  server.close(() => process.exit(0));\n});\n\nprocess.on('SIGINT', () => {\n  console.log('[scorer] SIGINT, shutting down');\n  server.close(() => process.exit(0));\n});\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58,"output":1338,"cacheRead":97123,"cacheWrite":313,"totalTokens":98832,"cost":{"input":0.0000174,"output":0.0016056,"cacheRead":0.005827379999999999,"cacheWrite":0.00011737500000000001,"total":0.007567755}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776483370550,"responseId":"06322f2a0dfee02154183334a3af3ad7"}}
