{"type":"message","id":"d0e4f0fb","parentId":"48aa1036","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:37:05.726Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, systemd user services need the `systemd` directory to be in the right place. For user-level systemd services, it should be at `~/.config/systemd/user/` not `~/.systemd/user/`. Let me check.\n\nActually, looking at the cron jobs and how they've been set up in this environment, I'm not sure if systemd user services are set up. Let me just use a simpler approach - start it as a background process with nohup or supervise it with a simple restart loop.\n\nActually, let me first create the log directory and then set up the systemd service properly. Let me check where user systemd services are stored.","thinkingSignature":"233e3da7c4fe561069f630b079b7847dcdb949b860bf8fe5deaf9919c762ff1c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yt7359tbliv0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p ~/.config/systemd/user\nmv ~/.systemd/user/openclaw-scorer.service ~/.config/systemd/user/\nmkdir -p ~/.openclaw/logs\nls ~/.config/systemd/user/"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":77600,"output":198,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99663,"cost":{"input":0.02328,"output":0.0002376,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0248295}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776483418386,"responseId":"06322f5af36ef981b6f8deafbf45e4d2"}}
