{"type":"message","id":"0660cff5","parentId":"274f251a","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:37:21.162Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The openclaw-v8.service points to `src/index.js` (the full v8 orchestrator) not the scorer. But I just confirmed that port 3103 has no listener (curl failed earlier). So the v8 service might be configured differently or not running.\n\nWait, but earlier the hook log showed `SCORE: 0` which means it tried to call 3103 and got a response (with score 0). Let me check if the openclaw-v8 service is running or if the scorer is already somehow working.Actually wait - when I tested the scorer server locally with `timeout 3 node scripts/scorer-server.js &`, it worked and returned score 41. But before that, the hook log showed `SCORE: 0` for the test message. \n\nSo either the hook hit a fallback path that returned 0, or something else was listening on 3103 at that point. Let me check the openclaw-v8 service status to see if it's actually running.","thinkingSignature":"d1246142e60f4257506e36bd7504239fc98aa85070551be1323f49625484c2fd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hcr82iqezug9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"systemctl --user status openclaw-v8.service 2>&1 | head -10\nsystemctl --user status openclaw-scorer.service 2>&1 | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":78237,"output":269,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100371,"cost":{"input":0.023471099999999998,"output":0.0003228,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0251058}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776483431586,"responseId":"06322f669cedcd21f4f19188b3def6da"}}
