{"type":"message","id":"12a3e94c","parentId":"e4d8f862","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:54:38.886Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The scorer returns 41 when called directly. But the hook gets 0. This means the hook is calling a different URL or parsing the response differently.\n\nLet me check the hook's runScoring function more carefully. The hook uses `http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score`. And `fetchJSON` uses `http.request`. Let me see if there's an issue with the hook's HTTP request or response parsing.\n\nActually wait - the log timestamp was `11:54:11`. But the scorer server started at 11:37. And there's no subagent announcement result yet. \n\nLet me check the hook's `runScoring` function. Looking at the handler.js I wrote earlier:\n\n\nThe function sends a POST request with the prompt in the body, but when I compare it to the curl command that works, the curl test shows it should return a score of 41. So the issue might be in how the hook is parsing the response or handling the HTTP request itself.","thinkingSignature":"21be47c4ea34fd3785d3285bc25cda91d9588efdcbf3613b1ed25dbbd930087d"},{"type":"text","text":"Scorer 返回 41，但 hook 得到 0。说明 hook 的 HTTP 调用有问题。检查 hook 的 fetchJSON：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f7og402a544a_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js | grep -A20 \"runScoring\\|SCORE\\|fetchJSON\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":79861,"output":284,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":102010,"cost":{"input":0.0239583,"output":0.0003408,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.025611}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776484471644,"responseId":"06323376c97a8127ff0d6cdd3b823bf8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"998582b8","parentId":"12a3e94c","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:54:39.366Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_f7og402a544a_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const SCORE_THRESHOLD = 40;\nconst SCORER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\";\nconst CLASSIFIER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\";\nconst HOOK_LOG = \"/tmp/auto-score-classify-hook.log\";\n\nfunction log(...args) {\n  const msg = `[${new Date().toISOString()}] ${args.join(\" \")}`;\n  console.log(msg);\n  fs.appendFileSync(HOOK_LOG, msg + \"\\n\");\n}\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 4000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      { method: \"POST\", headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) } },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => { try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); } catch { resolve(null); } });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(SCORER_URL, { prompt }, 4000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") return;\n\n  const text = event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\";\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) return;\n\n  // 跳过已经是 AUTO_ROUTE 的消息\n  if (text.startsWith(\"[AUTO_ROUTE]\")) {\n    log(\"SKIP: already has [AUTO_ROUTE] prefix\");\n    return;\n  }\n\n  log(`ORIGINAL TEXT: \"${text.slice(0, 100)}\"`);\n\n--\n    runScoring(text),\n    new Promise(r => setTimeout(() => r(null), 3000)),\n  ]);\n\n  const scoring = scoringResult;\n  const score = scoring?.score ?? 0;\n\n  log(`SCORE: ${score} (threshold=${SCORE_THRESHOLD})`);\n\n  if (score >= SCORE_THRESHOLD) {\n    const originalText = text;\n    event.context.bodyForAgent = `[AUTO_ROUTE] ${text}`;\n    log(`INJECTED: \"[AUTO_ROUTE] ${originalText.slice(0, 80)}...\"`);\n    log(`MODIFIED bodyForAgent: \"${event.context.bodyForAgent.slice(0, 100)}\"`);\n  } else {\n    log(`NO INJECTION: score ${score} < ${SCORE_THRESHOLD}`);\n  }\n\n  // 写 context.json\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n  ensureDir(sessionDir);\n  try {\n    fs.writeFileSync(path.join(sessionDir, \"context.json\"), JSON.stringify({ scoring, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() }, null, 2));\n  } catch {}\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":268,"aggregated":"const SCORE_THRESHOLD = 40;\nconst SCORER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\";\nconst CLASSIFIER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\";\nconst HOOK_LOG = \"/tmp/auto-score-classify-hook.log\";\n\nfunction log(...args) {\n  const msg = `[${new Date().toISOString()}] ${args.join(\" \")}`;\n  console.log(msg);\n  fs.appendFileSync(HOOK_LOG, msg + \"\\n\");\n}\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 4000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      { method: \"POST\", headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) } },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => { try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); } catch { resolve(null); } });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(SCORER_URL, { prompt }, 4000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") return;\n\n  const text = event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\";\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) return;\n\n  // 跳过已经是 AUTO_ROUTE 的消息\n  if (text.startsWith(\"[AUTO_ROUTE]\")) {\n    log(\"SKIP: already has [AUTO_ROUTE] prefix\");\n    return;\n  }\n\n  log(`ORIGINAL TEXT: \"${text.slice(0, 100)}\"`);\n\n--\n    runScoring(text),\n    new Promise(r => setTimeout(() => r(null), 3000)),\n  ]);\n\n  const scoring = scoringResult;\n  const score = scoring?.score ?? 0;\n\n  log(`SCORE: ${score} (threshold=${SCORE_THRESHOLD})`);\n\n  if (score >= SCORE_THRESHOLD) {\n    const originalText = text;\n    event.context.bodyForAgent = `[AUTO_ROUTE] ${text}`;\n    log(`INJECTED: \"[AUTO_ROUTE] ${originalText.slice(0, 80)}...\"`);\n    log(`MODIFIED bodyForAgent: \"${event.context.bodyForAgent.slice(0, 100)}\"`);\n  } else {\n    log(`NO INJECTION: score ${score} < ${SCORE_THRESHOLD}`);\n  }\n\n  // 写 context.json\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n  ensureDir(sessionDir);\n  try {\n    fs.writeFileSync(path.join(sessionDir, \"context.json\"), JSON.stringify({ scoring, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() }, null, 2));\n  } catch {}\n}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776484479297}}
{"type":"message","id":"f4e0510b","parentId":"998582b8","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:54:56.337Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see a critical issue: The hook uses `Promise.race` between `runScoring(text)` and a 3-second timeout. But `runScoring` itself has a 4-second timeout inside `fetchJSON`. So the total maximum wait could be 7 seconds, but the outer race only gives 3 seconds!\n\nAlso, the hook handler code is missing the concurrent call structure I thought I had written. Let me look at the full handler again.\n\nActually wait - the log shows `SCORE: 0` and `NO INJECTION: score 0 < 40`. The scoringResult is probably resolving with an object that has `score: 0` or `null`. \n\nThe issue might be that `scoringResult` is returning `null` from the timeout race, and then `scoring?.score ?? 0` defaults to 0. I should verify whether the timeout is actually firing and cutting off the scoring call before it completes.\n\nLooking at the request structure, the payload being sent to the scoring API is `{ prompt: text }`, which should match what the server expects. The server then extracts the prompt and passes it to `scoreTask()` to compute the result.\n\nThe 3-second timeout on the race might be too aggressive if the scorer is still initializing—the server process started around 11:37, and the first scoring request came in at 11:54, which is plenty of time. But the real problem could be that the hook is actually calling the wrong endpoint. The original scoring module was at `http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score`, and my new scorer server should be handling that same endpoint, so there might be a mismatch in what's actually being called.\n\nLooking at the hook's fetch logic more carefully, I notice the response data is only being accumulated from the HTTP response stream, but there's no timeout set on the request itself—if the connection hangs, the promise never resolves and the race condition defaults to `null`.\n\nBut actually, the real issue might be simpler: the hook is calling `runScoring(text)` with just the prompt, but the original message is \"分析 ~/.openclaw/hooks 目录下所有 hook 的功能、依赖和调用关系，生成一份完整架构文档\". When I test directly with curl it works and returns 41, yet the hook gets 0. Either there's an encoding problem, the request is timing out even with the 4-second limit, or the hook is silently failing and returning `null`.\n\nLet me look at the hook's log file to see what's actually happening.","thinkingSignature":"2827bd98f9e7d031b9691519a7318473a3a022701c982b7ba1be1eeb648443ed"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vkwqsqycw0kf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /tmp/auto-score-classify-hook.log | tail -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":80883,"output":567,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":103315,"cost":{"input":0.0242649,"output":0.0006804,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0262572}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776484479369,"responseId":"0632337fbd35acc58bf6700736897a40"}}
