{"type":"message","id":"273c6645","parentId":"b337135d","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:55:27.541Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The hook log shows it IS running and getting SCORE: 0 for every message. But the scorer at 3103 works when called via curl. The issue must be in the hook's HTTP request.\n\nWait - the hook is getting SCORE: 0 consistently, even for messages before the scorer server was started (11:37). So the hook was already getting 0 before the scorer was running. That means the 3103 was NOT running before 11:37, and the hook was calling it and getting some kind of error/timeout, resulting in `scoring?.score ?? 0 = 0`.\n\nBut now the scorer IS running (since 11:37). \n\nAnd the hook is STILL getting 0, even though the direct curl test returns 41. This points to a problem with how the hook is making the HTTP request. Let me check the hook's scoring function - it's passing `{ prompt: text }` to `fetchJSON`, which should work with the scorer's expected format.\n\nThe issue might be timing-related. The hook uses `Promise.race` with a 3-second timeout, but if the scorer is slow to respond or the request is hanging, it could be hitting that timeout and defaulting to 0. The `fetchJSON` function itself has a 4-second timeout, so if the outer race wins before the inner one resolves, we'd get a null result that becomes 0.\n\nBut looking at the actual response times in the logs—around 50ms between starting the scoring call and getting a result—those are way too fast for a timeout. So the problem isn't a timeout issue at all.\n\nThe hook is getting `scoringResult` back as `null`, which means the HTTP request to the scoring server is failing silently. I should add better error logging to the hook to see what's actually happening with the request, and maybe test connecting to `127.0.0.1:3103` directly to verify the server is reachable from the hook's context.\n\nLooking more carefully at the hook's fetch logic, I'm using `http.request` with the correct POST method and headers, so the request itself should be fine. But when I check the actual server implementation, I need to verify it's actually listening on the right port and handling requests properly. I see the issue now - the hook is making requests to `http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score`, but the server only responds to that exact path. The problem is that when the URL gets parsed with `req.url`, it's probably coming through as `/api/score` but I need to verify what the actual request path is when it reaches the server.\n\nLet me add some debugging to the hook to see what URL is actually being requested and what the response looks like. The hook's `fetchJSON` function isn't logging errors, so network failures would silently resolve as `null` - that's likely why the hook keeps getting 0 for the score.\n\nI should rewrite the hook with better error logging and switch to `axios` instead, since `auto-score-classify` already depends on it anyway.","thinkingSignature":"dabb52f08e94656f9a2a1a2589486737de09ea9c9c3997c59eeb302cfa4c4433"},{"type":"text","text":"Hook 始终返回 0，但 curl 返回 41。问题在 hook 的 HTTP 调用本身。添加详细日志诊断：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i0dczjx12v61_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js","content":"// auto-score-classify hook v5 - 带详细诊断日志\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\nimport { createRequire } from \"node:module\";\n\nconst require = createRequire(import.meta.url);\nconst axios = require(\"axios\");\n\nconst SCORE_THRESHOLD = 40;\nconst SCORER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\";\nconst CLASSIFIER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\";\n\nfunction log(...args) {\n  const msg = `[${new Date().toISOString()}] ${args.join(\" \")}`;\n  console.log(msg);\n  fs.appendFileSync(\"/tmp/auto-score-classify-hook.log\", msg + \"\\n\");\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  try {\n    const res = await axios.post(SCORER_URL, { prompt }, { timeout: 5000 });\n    log(`SCORER_OK: ${JSON.stringify(res.data).slice(0, 100)}`);\n    return res.data;\n  } catch (err) {\n    log(`SCORER_ERR: ${err.message} | code=${err.code} | status=${err.response?.status}`);\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  try {\n    const res = await axios.post(CLASSIFIER_URL, { text }, { timeout: 5000 });\n    return res.data;\n  } catch (err) {\n    log(`CLASSIFIER_ERR: ${err.message}`);\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") return;\n\n  const text = event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\";\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) return;\n\n  if (text.startsWith(\"[AUTO_ROUTE]\")) {\n    log(\"SKIP: already has [AUTO_ROUTE]\");\n    return;\n  }\n\n  log(`MSG: \"${text.slice(0, 80)}\"`);\n\n  const [classification, scoring] = await Promise.all([\n    runClassification(text),\n    runScoring(text),\n  ]);\n\n  const score = scoring?.score ?? 0;\n  log(`RESULT: score=${score} scene=${classification?.scene} strategy=${scoring?.recommendedStrategy}`);\n\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n  ensureDir(sessionDir);\n\n  // 写 context.json\n  try {\n    fs.writeFileSync(path.join(sessionDir, \"context.json\"), JSON.stringify({ classification, scoring, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() }, null, 2));\n  } catch {}\n\n  if (score >= SCORE_THRESHOLD) {\n    event.context.bodyForAgent = `[AUTO_ROUTE] ${text}`;\n    log(`INJECTED [AUTO_ROUTE] (score=${score} >= ${SCORE_THRESHOLD})`);\n  } else {\n    log(`NO INJECT: score ${score} < ${SCORE_THRESHOLD}`);\n  }\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"inp