{"type":"message","id":"11d689a8","parentId":"06f1daa6","timestamp":"2026-04-18T03:57:44.163Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Key observations from the log:\n\n1. Gateway restarted (11:55) but there's NO \"loaded N internal hook handlers\" message and NO \"SCORER_OK/SCORER_ERR\" in the log\n2. The hook's console.log output goes to `subsystem-Cgmckbux.js` which means it IS running through the gateway's logging system\n3. But there are no hook logs after the restart!\n\nWait - looking more carefully, the gateway log after 11:55 doesn't show \"loaded N internal hook handlers\" or any SCORER_OK messages. But looking at the earlier logs, the hook WAS running before the restart.\n\n\nThe sessions_send succeeded (got a timeout response which means the agent responded), but there's no hook log output since the restart. I'm not seeing the \"loaded N internal hook handlers\" line from gateway startup either, which suggests either the hook didn't load or its output isn't being captured. The v5 handler uses `import.meta.url` with `createRequire` for axios, but gateway hooks run as ES modules without the npm package resolution needed, so axios probably isn't available. I should switch to the native http module instead and also check if the hook is actually being registered by looking for the \"loaded internal hook handlers\" message.","thinkingSignature":"2e8ae5135bbc74d639943997db5fc4c254474ba728484551682566f473b86f56"},{"type":"text","text":"Gateway 重启后 hook 没有日志输出——说明 hook 根本没加载。需要确认 workspace hooks 是否被 gateway 正确扫描：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r72a19gq0owq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -i \"loaded.*hook\\|workspace.*hook\\|hook.*load\\|auto-score\" /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-18.log | tail -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91002,"output":344,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113211,"cost":{"input":0.027300599999999998,"output":