{"type":"message","id":"245c29f0","parentId":"8dc4e13b","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:00:02.742Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! Now I can see what's happening clearly:\n\n1. Hook loaded successfully (6 handlers loaded at 11:58:25)\n2. Hook IS RUNNING (SCORER log at 11:59:18)\n3. SCORER returned `{\"score\":0,\"factors\":...}` — same problem as before!\n4. Hook uses native http module now (no axios error)\n\nBut the scorer STILL returns 0 via the hook, while curl returns 41.\n\nWait - look at the scorer result: `{\"score\":0,\"factors\":{\"logic\":0,\"risk\":0,\"duration\":0,\"resource\":0,\"uncertainty\":0,\"dependency\":0},\"` - it's 0 for ALL factors! But when I curl with `{\"prompt\":\"...\"}` I get score 41.\n \nAh, I see the issue now — the hook is sending the text as the `text` property since it calls the classification endpoint, but the scorer is actually looking for `prompt` in the scoring function. So when the hook makes its request to the scorer, it's probably not formatting the payload correctly for what the scoring endpoint expects.\n\nBut wait, that doesn't quite add up either. If the scorer is using `scoreTask()` from the scoring module, it's extracting the prompt with `const prompt = body.prompt || body.text || ...`. So if the hook sends `{ prompt: text }` like it does for the classification endpoint, the scorer should find it in the `prompt` field.\n\nLet me trace through the actual hook code to see what's really being sent. Looking at the scoring response with all factors at 0 and only the raw total showing, this points to the `scoreTask()` function receiving an empty or whitespace-only prompt string. The early return condition `const text = prompt || ''` would cause `text` to be empty, resulting in zero scores across all factors since no patterns would match. But the hook IS logging that a message was received, so the prompt shouldn't be empty. This suggests something is stripping or truncating the prompt value between when the hook logs it and when it reaches the scoring function. The logging shows the scorer returned all zeros, which means either the scorer itself isn't detecting the Chinese text properly, or there's something wrong with how the prompt is being passed to the scoring function. I should add more detailed logging to see the actual prompt value the scorer receives, or check if there's an issue with how the message text is being extracted from the event context before it gets to the scorer.","thinkingSignature":"7bc6501b47d078b8b52bcba05f56892d425c66fb83ee2fc56d11c81d5bc8c754"},{"type":"text","text":"**Hook 已加载！** 6 handlers loaded。但 scorer 返回全 0。问题在 scorer 端或传参。诊断 scorer 对中文消息的实际行为：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sn5kshbvk9dv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3103/api/score -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"prompt\":\"分析 ~/.openclaw/hooks 目录下所有 hook 的功能、依赖和调用关系，生成一份完整架构文档\"}' --max-time 3\necho \"\"\n# Also test with \"text\" field\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3103/api/score -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"分析 ~/.openclaw/hooks 目录下所有 hook 的功能、依赖和调用关系\"}' --max-time 3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":95906,"output":696,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":118467,"cost":{"input":0.0287718,"output":0.0008351999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.030918900000000003}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776484782451,"responseId":"063234ac1960651202da5ed59279efc2"}}
