{"type":"message","id":"4d1064f7","parentId":"4ebe1f03","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:00:37.222Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both `prompt` and `text` fields work correctly from curl. The scorer returns 41 with `prompt` and 24 with `text`.\n\nSo the scorer works fine via curl. But the hook's native http call returns `{\"score\":0,...}`. \n\nLet me look at the scorer-server.js code more carefully. The issue might be that when the hook sends `{ prompt: text }`, and the scorer receives it and passes it to `scoreTask()`, something goes wrong.\n\nActually wait - let me look at the hook's `fetchJSON` more carefully:\n\n```javascript\nconst req = http.request(\n  url,\n  {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n  },\n  (res) => {\n    let data = \"\";\n    res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n    res.on(\"end\", () => {\n      try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); }\n      catch { resolve(null); }\n    });\n  }\n);\n```\n\nI'm using `Buffer.byteLength` from the Node.js buffer module to calculate the Content-Length header, which should work fine in the Node.js environment where this code runs.\n\nLet me trace through what the scorer-server actually receives when the hook sends a request. I'm wondering if the issue might be with how `event.context?.bodyForAgent` is being passed—maybe it's not a string at all but some other data type that would stringify to something unexpected. I should add logging to the hook's fetchJSON to see the exact postData being sent, or add a debug endpoint to the scorer to log what it actually receives. Let me try calling the scorer directly from the hook using Node.js exec to isolate whether the problem is in the HTTP layer or something else.\n\nWait, I just noticed something in the gateway log—the hook logged `SCORER: {\"score\":0,\"factors\":{\"logic\":0,...` with the response truncated at 100 characters, which means the scorer is actually returning score 0, not that the HTTP request itself is failing. Let me look at the full scorer response more carefully.\n\nThe response shows all factors are 0, which means the `scoreTask()` function is receiving the prompt but it's matching zero patterns. That's strange because when I test it via curl with the same prompt, it returns score 41. So something in the hook's execution context is different from my terminal environment. Maybe the gateway process has a different working directory or environment that's affecting how the scoring function behaves. is different from the hook's environment. Let me think...\n\nThe scorer server runs as a separate process (PID 5572 via systemd). The hook runs inside the gateway process. Both are Node.js.\n\nWait, let me look at the scorer-server.js code again. It uses `require('../src/scoring/scoring')`. The working directory is `/home/ai/.openclaw/v8`. And scoring.js has `module.exports`. When the scorer requires scoring.js, it gets the scoring module.\n\nBut what if the issue is with how the hook is sending data? Let me look at the scorer-server's `parseBody` function - it concatenates all chunks and parses the result, which should work correctly.\n\nWait, I think I see it now. The hook uses `http.request` without specifying `hostname`, so it defaults to localhost. But the scorer is listening on `0.0.0.0`, which should accept connections from any interface. The connection should succeed, but maybe something's wrong with how the request is being formatted or sent.\n\nLet me add a test directly in the hook to log the exact data being sent and verify the scorer is actually receiving what we expect. Or I could use `exec` to run a quick curl command from within the hook's context to see what's actually happening. Actually, let me just write a simpler diagnostic approach - have the hook itself call the scorer with a known prompt and log the result to see if the issue is with the request or the response handling.","thinkingSignature":"a097bcdcf995d53ee0b98b4fa4cef1f77739c402a6f8c82070e50af2c1d92382"},{"type":"text","text":"Hook 返回 0 但 curl 返回 41。说明 scorer 本身没问题，是 hook 的调用方式有问题。添加更精确的诊断到 hook 里：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wknb4ayxvnj6_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js","content":"// auto-score-classify hook v7 - 精确定位 scorer 返回 0 的问题\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nconst SCORE_THRESHOLD = 40;\nconst SCORER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\";\nconst CLASSIFIER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\";\n\nfunction log(...args) {\n  console.log(`[hook] ${new Date().toISOString()} ${args.join(\" \")}`);\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") return;\n\n  const text = String(event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\");\n  if (!text.trim()) return;\n\n  if (text.startsWith(\"[AUTO_ROUTE]\")) {\n    log(\"SKIP: already has [AUTO_ROUTE]\");\n    return;\n  }\n\n  log(`MSG: \"${text.slice(0, 60)}...\"`);\n\n  // ── 直接在 hook 里 require scoring.js 测试 ──\n  try {\n    const scoring = await import(\"/home/ai/.openclaw/v8/src/scoring/scoring.js\");\n    const result = scoring.scoreTask(text);\n    log(`DIRECT_SCORE: score=${result.score} factors=${JSON.stringify(result.factors)}`);\n    log(`DIRECT_STRATEGY: ${result.recommendedStrategy}`);\n\n    const score = result.score ?? 0;\n\n    const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n    const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n    if (!fs.existsSync(sessionDir)) fs.mkdirSync(sessionDir, { recursive: true });\n    fs.writeFileSync(path.join(sessionDir, \"context.json\"), JSON.stringify({\n      scoring: result,\n      classification: null,\n      timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n    }, null, 2));\n\n    if (score >= SCORE_THRESHOLD) {\n      event.context.bodyForAgent = `[AUTO_ROUTE] ${text}`;\n      log(`INJECTED [AUTO_ROUTE] (score=${score} >= ${SCORE_THRESHOLD})`);\n    } else {\n      log(`NO_INJECT: score ${score} < ${SCORE_THRESHOLD}`);\n    }\n  } catch (err) {\n    log(`ERROR: ${err.message}`);\n  }\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":96727,"output":1426,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120018,"cost":{"input":0.029018099999999998,"output":0.0017112,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0320412}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776484803220,"responseId":"063234c15a69e238dd0fe1cfff6a8ca1"}}
