{"type":"message","id":"9378228d","parentId":"c228e6fe","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:03:32.357Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both `require()` and `import()` return 41. So the issue must be with the `text` that the hook is actually receiving.\n\nThe hook message says: `\"MSG: \\\"[Sat 2026-04-18 12:01 GMT+8] 你在干什么老是干一半就停了\\\"\"`\n\nSo the text being scored IS \"你在干什么老是干一半就停了\" (the user message). But this is the user's complaint message, not the \"分析 ~/.openclaw/hooks 目录\" message!\n\nThe `sessions_send` message didn't reach the hook. The hook is only seeing the user's complaint message about \"干一半就停了\".\n\nLet me check what messages actually reached the hook. The only hook log entry was for \"你在干什么老是干一半就停了\". This is because sessions_send was used to send \"分析 ~/.openclaw/hooks 目录，生成完整架构文档\" - but it timed out, and the agent responded to the complaint instead, so the original task message might not have been processed as a hook message.\n\n\nActually, wait - sessions_send does trigger the hook. But looking at the logs, the only thing captured was the user's complaint message. The task message \"分析 ~/.openclaw/hooks 目录，生成完整架构文档\" might not have reached the hook at all, or it was the user's complaint that came through instead.\n\nI need to send the task message again and watch the logs to see if it actually triggers the hook and what score it gets.","thinkingSignature":"182bfc7ddfd6b9418cb91be5d1c366b8a4f8a30e0e301fcada9db897fd9d7a3d"},{"type":"text","text":"原来 hook 收到的是\"你在干什么老是干一半就停了\"（你的抱怨消息），不是任务消息。sessions_send 的任务消息可能没触发 hook。让我重新发一条真正的任务消息：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_85d8laqe41is_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:main:main","message":"帮我写一个Python快速排序"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":101069,"output":392,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123326,"cost":{"input":0.0303207,"output":0.0004704,"cacheRead":0.0013119,