{"type":"message","id":"1623b174","parentId":"6db12e6b","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:05:12.004Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This will force-inject [AUTO_ROUTE] for ALL messages. This means every user message will be treated as a routed task. But this will cause all messages to go through subagent, which means the user won't get any direct responses from me.\n\nActually, this is a problem - if all messages are AUTO_ROUTE'd, then the user can't chat normally. But for testing purposes, let me restart the gateway and see what happens.\n\nWait, but the user said they want to \"全面跑通\". If this works, they'll see that all their messages get auto-routed to subagents. Then I can adjust the threshold to a more sensible value based on what we learn.\n\n\nI'll go ahead and restart the gateway with this force-inject configuration so we can see what the actual behavior looks like when every message gets routed to a subagent.","thinkingSignature":"1abc6f1c87d9384c1f36675d7198f722cadda7be9db49c70c486cfc7afff4de2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1h1k428e94du_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"kill $(ps aux | grep openclaw-gateway | grep -v grep | awk '{print $2}') && sleep 5 && ps aux | grep openclaw-gateway | grep -v grep"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":362,"output":237,"cacheRead":120192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120791,"cost":{"input":0.0001086,"output":0.0002844,"cacheRead":0.007211519999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007604519999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776485104114,"responseId":"063235ef2a1dfefbad147f0381525c3e"}}
