{"type":"message","id":"fbf2eebf","parentId":"bd5585f8","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:07:30.668Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sat 2026-04-18 12:07 GMT+8] 发挥你的主观能动性，我需要全面跑通，执行任何前，必须进行思考"}],"timestamp":1776485250610}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca5c1f7f","parentId":"fbf2eebf","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:07:55.920Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to keep going and get the full system operational. They've been frustrated by me stopping mid-action repeatedly.\n\nCurrent state:\n- Hook is injecting [AUTO_ROUTE] for ALL messages (force mode, threshold=0)\n- But the issue is that `sessions_send` doesn't trigger the `message:preprocessed` hook\n- The user sees my (the agent's) replies, not subagent results, because the hook isn't intercepting messages from `sessions_send`\n\nThe real question is: does the hook intercept messages from the actual webchat channel? Based on earlier logs, the hook DID fire for the user's complaint message (\"你在干什么老是干一半就停了\"), which came from webchat. So for real webchat messages, the hook fires.\n \nThe user wants full automation where every task-type message automatically gets routed to a subagent without the main agent responding. The current setup forces all messages through [AUTO_ROUTE], but the main agent is still replying because the hook modifications aren't preventing the agent from generating responses—the injected prefix just gets added to the message content without actually redirecting it. I need to verify whether this is actually working end-to-end or if something's blocking the routing.\n\nSince `sessions_send` doesn't trigger the `message:preprocessed` hook, I should test this directly through the webchat interface instead of trying to simulate it. The user could send a simple message like \"帮我写一个Python快排\" to see if it properly routes to a subagent and returns only the subagent's response without my reply. Alternatively, if the current force-mode setup with threshold=0 is causing issues, I could revert to a smarter scoring approach that uses the HTTP endpoint instead of relying on direct module imports, which had the CJS/ESM problem.\n\nThe real solution is to parse the scoring.js output format carefully and make sure the HTTP request sends the prompt in the correct structure that the scoring endpoint expects. curl returned 41 for this exact message, so the issue is specifically in how the hook is making the HTTP request. The problem might be with Content-Length, timeout too short, or some other request issue.\n\nLet me go back to the HTTP approach but with an explicit test: write a simple test script that makes the same HTTP call the hook would make, with the exact same text, to see if we can reproduce the 0 vs 41 difference.\n\nActually, I think the core issue is that I'm spending too much time debugging instead of just getting things working. The simplest path forward is to remove the axios dependency and native http module entirely, then either use the subprocess approach to invoke node with the scoring script directly, or revert to scoring.js without CJS/ESM complications.\n\nBut let me step back and test the actual HTTP call the hook would make to see what's really happening.","thinkingSignature":"5d27ac42c8f32fc0cc73de7f2e6675b8d5f4af2ef443d792e544916fd2c445ed"},{"type":"text","text":"### 思考\n\n问题是：hook 里 HTTP 调用 scorer 返回 0，但 curl 返回 41。直接对比两种调用的差异。让我精确定位。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1abtp7ka4oyn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 精确复现 hook 的 HTTP 调用\nnode -e \"\nconst http = require('http');\nconst text = '分析 ~/.openclaw/hooks 目录，生成完整架构文档';\nconst postData = JSON.stringify({ prompt: text });\nconsole.log('POST_DATA:', postData.slice(0, 80));\nconst req = http.request(\n  'http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score',\n  { method: 'POST', headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Content-Length': Buffer.byteLength(postData) } },\n  (res) => {\n    let data = '';\n    res.on('data', c => data += c);\n    res.on('end', () => console.log('RESULT:', data.slice(0, 100)));\n  }\n);\nreq.on('error', e => console.error('ERR:', e.message));\nreq.write(postData);\nreq.end();\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58,"output":820,"cacheRead":126553,"cacheWrite":947,"totalTokens":128378,"cost":{"input":0.0000174,"output":0.0009839999999999998,"cacheRead":0.00759318,"cacheWrite":0.000355125,"total":0.008949704999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776485250741,"responseId":"06323680b994813a9a7604ffd2d5be26"}}
{"type":"message","id":"905a7f6d","parentId":"ca5c1f7f","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:07:56.494Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1abtp7ka4oyn_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"POST_DATA: {\"prompt\":\"分析 ~/.openclaw/hooks 目录，生成完整架构文档\"}\nRESULT: {\"score\":41,\"factors\":{\"logic\":2,\"risk\":0,\"duration\":1,\"resource\":0,\"uncertainty\":0,\"dependency\":0},"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":246,"aggregated":"POST_DATA: {\"prompt\":\"分析 ~/.openclaw/hooks 目录，生成完整架构文档\"}\nRESULT: {\"score\":41,\"factors\":{\"logic\":2,\"risk\":0,\"duration\":1,\"resource\":0,\"uncertainty\":0,\"dependency\":0},","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776485276379}}
{"type":"message","id":"cd5c6e8c","parentId":"905a7f6d","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:08:03.150Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The HTTP call works fine from node directly. So the issue must be that the hook's `await import()` is loading a different version of scoring.js, or the `event.context?.bodyForAgent` in the hook is different from what I think.\n\nWait - but now with force mode (threshold=0), the hook just injects [AUTO_ROUTE] without calling the scorer. So the HTTP issue is irrelevant now. The question is whether the hook is correctly modifying `event.context.bodyForAgent`.\n\nLet me check if there's a new log entry after the restart:","thinkingSignature":"86d5cac4666d95c9a67f00263eb3a7397bb131346240ca959aaa2dc89c24d993"},{"type":"text","text":"HTTP 调用完全正常，返回 41。hook 的 HTTP 没问题。那现在 force mode（阈值=0）下 hook 必定注入前缀。检查最新日志：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iqwuge7c5f80_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep \"hook.*INJECTED\\|loaded.*hook\" /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-18.log | tail -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":106583,"output":204,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128652,"cost":{"input":0.0319749,"output":0.0002448,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0335316}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776485276498,"responseId":"0632369a35a48ab895cb50b0ecbba65f"}}
