{"type":"message","id":"e018427a","parentId":"9bc79ffa","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:11:52.456Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user sent \"？\" asking what's happening. The subagent task should have completed by now. Let me check if there was any result pushed. Actually, the subagent should have completed and pushed results to webchat. But the user is asking \"?\" which means they haven't seen results either.\n\nLet me check the status of things. The hook is injecting [AUTO_ROUTE] on ALL messages now (threshold=0), which means every time the user sends a message, the hook modifies it to start with [AUTO_ROUTE], and then the main agent's SOUL.md matches it and tries to spawn... but the main agent's sessions_send messages don't trigger the hook.\n \nThe subagent finished its work a few minutes ago and pushed results to webchat. Since there's no completion event showing in the conversation, the user should have seen those results appear in their interface. The \"?\" is likely them asking for status, not indicating a problem. Let me just provide a status update without requesting more information.","thinkingSignature":"67992324e07544cae4ba2fac7fa8e74c34c311c8fc279aeb8e6a0b75e0009977"},{"type":"text","text":"子 agent 任务应该已完成并在 webchat 推送了结果。你在 webchat 界面里应该已经看到了吗？\n\n如果没有，可能是推送出了问题。我这边直接输出子 agent 的执行结果：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8siwo937a0hx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:subagent:a020f027-9ee8-4a77-8bad-d22108ec68a9/history.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor m in d[-5:]:\n    role=m.get('role','')\n    content=m.get('content','')\n    if role=='assistant' and content:\n        print(content[:500])\n        print('---')\n\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"No history file\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58,"output":385,"cacheRead":128106,"cacheWrite":1513,"totalTokens":13006