{"type":"message","id":"1e1ea811","parentId":"4967701e","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:21:28.439Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to deploy context-monitor hook. Let me think about this carefully.\n\nContext-monitor's job:\n- Monitor session context size (token count)\n- Trigger auto-compression when threshold exceeded\n- Events: `message:preprocessed`, `agent:response`\n- Config from `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` → `context.*` nodes\n- Token calculation: `ceil(chinese_chars / 1.5) + ceil(other_chars / 4)`\n- Compression algorithm: preserve recent N turns, summarize the rest\n\nI need to:\n1. Read the existing context-monitor handler to understand its current state\n2. Fix any issues preventing it from loading\n3. Ensure it reads config properly from openclaw.json\n4. Deploy and verify\n\nLet me first check the existing context-monitor implementation and the context config in openclaw.json.","thinkingSignature":"9a7eaf30358fbec4a72ef0c493342a8eab05d0fedede9e5bfb225ac86b3b3e50"},{"type":"text","text":"\n### 思考\n\ncontext-monitor 的核心逻辑：监听 `message:preprocessed` + `agent:response`，当 context token 超限时压缩。需要检查：现有 handler 实现、config 格式、为什么没被加载。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5gao5bbn24cu_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/context-monitor/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58,"output":262,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":32492,"totalTokens":54677,"cost":{"input":0.0000174,"output":0.0003144,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0.012184500000000001,"total":0.0138282}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776486081275,"responseId":"063239bfcef38843a237b11093e20b14"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9ad11949","parentId":"1e1ea811","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:21:28.851Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5gao5bbn24cu_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * Context Monitor Hook\n * 监控 session context 大小，超过阈值时触发自动压缩\n */\n\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\n\nconst CONFIG_PATH = '/home/ai/.openclaw/openclaw.json';\nconst SESSION_CONTEXT_PATH = process.env.OPENCLAW_SESSION_CONTEXT_PATH || \n  path.join(process.env.OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR || '/home/ai/.openclaw', 'sessions/agent:main:main/context.json');\n\nfunction loadConfig() {\n  try {\n    const config = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(CONFIG_PATH, 'utf8'));\n    const ctx = config.context || {};\n    return {\n      maxTokens: ctx.maxContextTokens || 160000,\n      threshold: ctx.summarizeThreshold || 0.75,\n      preserveRecent: ctx.preserveRecentTurns || 10,\n      enabled: ctx.monitoringEnabled !== false\n    };\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction countTokens(text) {\n  if (!text) return 0;\n  const chinese = (text.match(/[\\u4e00-\\u9fa5]/g) || []).length;\n  const other = text.length - chinese;\n  return Math.ceil(chinese / 1.5 + other / 4);\n}\n\nfunction countSessionTokens(messages) {\n  return messages.reduce((sum, m) => {\n    return sum + countTokens(m.content || '') + countTokens(m.name || '') + 20;\n  }, 0);\n}\n\nasync function compactSession(messages, config) {\n  const systemMsgs = messages.filter(m => m.role === 'system');\n  const recentMsgs = messages.slice(-config.preserveRecent);\n  const oldMsgs = messages.slice(0, -config.preserveRecent);\n  \n  // 生成摘要\n  const oldText = oldMsgs.map(m => `${m.role}: ${(m.content || '').slice(0, 200)}`).join('\\n');\n  const summary = oldText.length > 2000 ? oldText.slice(0, 2000) + '...' : oldText;\n  \n  const summaryMsg = {\n    role: 'system',\n    content: `[Previous conversation summary - ${oldMsgs.length} messages condensed]: ${summary}`\n  };\n  \n  return [...systemMsgs, summaryMsg, ...recentMsgs];\n}\n\nasync function main() {\n  const config = loadConfig();\n  if (!config || !config.enabled) {\n    console.log('[context-monitor] disabled or no config');\n    return;\n  }\n  \n  try {\n    const sessionData = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(SESSION_CONTEXT_PATH, 'utf8'));\n    const messages = sessionData.messages || [];\n    \n    const currentTokens = countSessionTokens(messages);\n    const limit = config.maxTokens * config.threshold;\n    \n    console.log(`[context-monitor] tokens=${currentTokens}/${limit} (${Math.round(currentTokens/limit*100)}%)`);\n    \n    if (currentTokens > limit) {\n      console.log(`[context-monitor] Threshold exceeded! Triggering compaction...`);\n      const compacted = await compactSession(messages, config);\n      sessionData.messages = compacted;\n      fs.writeFileSync(SESSION_CONTEXT_PATH, JSON.stringify(sessionData, null, 2));\n      console.log(`[context-monitor] Compaction done: ${messages.length} -> ${compacted.length} messages`);\n    }\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`[context-monitor] Error: ${err.message}`);\n  }\n}\n\nmain();\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776486088765}}
{"type":"message","id":"90f8c756","parentId":"9ad11949","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:21:36.104Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The current context-monitor handler.js uses CommonJS (`require`) and is designed as a standalone CLI script, not as a hook event handler. It doesn't export an async function `handler(event)` that the gateway expects.\n\nThe context-monitor hook needs to be rewritten to:\n1. Export a default async function `handler(event)` \n2. Handle the gateway hook event format\n3. Use the `event.sessionKey` to find the right session context file instead of hardcoding `agent:main:main`\n4. Run on both `message:preprocessed` and `agent:response` events\n\nLet me also check if the openclaw.json has context config.","thinkingSignature":"34760a5dbfc4a9d5094426f23bcc072222b8166c8fa3568c77d90f4b84ce3912"},{"type":"text","text":"问题找到了：handler.js 是 CJS 格式的 CLI 脚本，不是 hook 格式。没有导出 `handler(event)` 函数。还需要动态定位 session context 文件。\n\n先检查 openclaw.json 里有没有 context 配置：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x09vmm8py7ae_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d.get('context', {}), indent=2))\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33569,"output":241,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55675,"cost":{"input":0.0100707,"output":0.0002892,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0116718}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776486088853,"responseId":"063239c85316064089267f79021e437d"}}
