{"type":"message","id":"e27c4279","parentId":"11569f02","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:21:46.144Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The context config is empty. I need to add it. Now let me think about what context-monitor needs to do:\n\n1. Rewrite handler.js to work as a proper hook event handler (export default async function handler(event))\n2. Add context config to openclaw.json\n3. The hardcoded session path is wrong - it should use event.sessionKey dynamically\n\nThe current handler has these issues:\n1. CJS format (require instead of import) - but gateway can load CJS so this might not be fatal\n2. Hardcoded path `sessions/agent:main:main/context.json` instead of dynamic per session\n3. No `handler` export - it's a main() function that runs on script load\n\n\n4. The hook event object provides `sessionKey` and `workspaceDir` through the event context, so I can use these to construct the correct path dynamically instead of hardcoding it\n5. I need to check how the gateway hook loader passes the session context path - if it's available in the event context I can use that directly rather than trying to derive it myself","thinkingSignature":"3e35a4da4e00ade22f209e7cdebd80ce0d1030e90f6a12ab9459e95e88ad569f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pimkyxthba2s_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 gateway 传给 hook 的 event context 里有什么路径信息\ngrep -r \"sessionEntry\\|contextFile\\|contextPath\\|OPENCLAW_SESSION\" /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-18.log 2>/dev/null | tail -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33827,"output":300,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55992,"cost":{"input":0.0101481,"output":0.00035999999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011819999999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776486096663,"responseId":"063239cfe5160bd1e73cfe4554f67116"}}
