{"type":"message","id":"51925365","parentId":"55b1c937","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:21:48.015Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No luck. Let me look at how session context files are stored. The context.json is in the session directory. Let me check the session directories.","thinkingSignature":"a5ef00843ef620c85e3b5fb35375b95776aab0a195ccde96317afd2fce03fc3f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tkouns731pik_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 找 session context 文件的真实路径\nfind ~/.openclaw/sessions -name \"context.json\" 2>/dev/null | head -5\nls ~/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:main/ 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34145,"output":102,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56112,"cost":{"input":0.0102435,"output":0.0001224,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011677799999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776486106713,"responseId":"063239d8c9b959a52bf9db58cf275fa0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"df60c34c","parentId":"51925365","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:21:48.532Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tkouns731pik_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:fast_agent:feishu:group:oc_1b955e738aa196d7f2afe9e1c1d35575/context.json\n/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:cron:8f74a423-555b-468d-aac3-f8822b65bbcb/context.json\n/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:coder:main/context.json\n/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:main/context.json\n/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:fast_agent:main/context.json\ncontext.json"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":247,"aggregated":"/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:fast_agent:feishu:group:oc_1b955e738aa196d7f2afe9e1c1d35575/context.json\n/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:cron:8f74a423-555b-468d-aac3-f8822b65bbcb/context.json\n/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:coder:main/context.json\n/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:main/context.json\n/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:fast_agent:main/context.json\ncontext.json","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776486108422}}
{"type":"message","id":"2b2f5526","parentId":"df60c34c","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:22:15.455Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The context.json files exist. For the main session, it's at `~/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:main/context.json`.\n\nNow let me think about what the hook needs to do:\n1. Intercept `message:preprocessed` events\n2. For each event, find the session's context.json\n3. Count tokens in the messages array\n4. If over threshold, compress\n\nThe tricky part: how does the hook know which session's context.json to read? The `event.sessionKey` gives us that.\n\nBut actually - context-monitor needs to run on `message:preprocessed` (before the agent processes the message) to do预防性压缩. \n\nSo when a message:preprocessed event fires, I need to read the current session's context.json from `~/.openclaw/sessions/{sessionKey}/context.json`, count the tokens, and compress if necessary. Though I'm realizing the event structure might not always have a bodyForAgent - for preprocessed messages it should, but I need to verify what the event context actually contains.\n\nThe bigger challenge is understanding the full architecture: whether there's a Context API at 3101 that the hook talks to, or if it directly modifies the context.json file. From the ARCHITECTURE.md, context-monitor watches `message:preprocessed` and `agent:response` events and relies on `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` for the context configuration.\n\nGiven that 3101 isn't running, I need to work without it. My approach will be to directly read and write the context.json file, export a handler function, dynamically resolve the session path from event.sessionKey, add the necessary context configuration to openclaw.json, and ensure proper error handling throughout.","thinkingSignature":"1bf9e275106d9d1cc6bd51244f02a434e70b351180586eb832bd73e1fbd33078"},{"type":"text","text":"好。context.json 路径格式是 `~/.openclaw/sessions/{sessionKey}/context.json`。现在重写 handler.js：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cflsre5hm9f3_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/context-monitor/handler.js","content":"/**\n * Context Monitor Hook - OpenClaw\n * 事件: message:preprocessed, agent:response\n * 功能: 监控 session context token 数量，超限时自动压缩\n */\nimport fs from 'node:fs';\nimport path from 'node:path';\n\nconst CONFIG_PATH = '/home/ai/.openclaw/openclaw.json';\n\nfunction loadConfig() {\n  try {\n    const raw = fs.readFileSync(CONFIG_PATH, 'utf8');\n    const config = JSON.parse(raw);\n    const ctx = config.context || {};\n    return {\n      maxTokens:          ctx.maxContextTokens      || 160000,\n      threshold:          ctx.summarizeThreshold    || 0.75,\n      preserveRecent:     ctx.preserveRecentTurns   || 10,\n      enabled:            ctx.monitoringEnabled !== false,\n    };\n  } catch {\n    // Config unreadable — default to disabled\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction countTokensForText(text) {\n  if (!text) return 0;\n  const chinese = (text.match(/[\\u4e00-\\u9fa5]/g) || []).length;\n  const other   = text.length - chinese;\n  return Math.ceil(chinese / 1.5 + other / 4);\n}\n\nfunction countSessionTokens(messages) {\n  return messages.reduce((sum, m) => {\n    return sum\n      + countTokensForText(m.content || '')\n      + countTokensForText(m.name    || '')\n      + 20; // overhead per message\n  }, 0);\n}\n\nfunction getContextPath(sessionKey) {\n  const base = process.env.OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR || '/home/ai/.openclaw';\n  // sessionKey format: agent:main:main  →  agent:main:main\n  // or agent:main:subagent:uuid\n  const safe = sessionKey.replace(/:/g, '_');\n  return path.join(base, 'sessions', safe, 'context.json');\n}\n\nasync function compress(messages, preserveRecent) {\n  const systemMsgs = messages.filter(m => m.role === 'system');\n  const recentMsgs = messages.slice(-preserveRecent);\n  const oldMsgs    = messages.slice(0, -preserveRecent);\n\n  // Build a single summary message from the old batch\n  const summaryContent = oldMsgs\n    .map(m => `${m.role}: ${(m.content || '').slice(0, 150)}`)\n    .join('\\n');\n\n  return [\n    ...systemMsgs,\n    {\n      role: 'system',\n      content: `[Compacted ${oldMsgs.length} previous messages]: ${summaryContent.slice(0, 2000)}`,\n    },\n    ...recentMsgs,\n  ];\n}\n\nasync function handleEvent(event) {\n  const config = loadConfig();\n  if (!config || !config.enabled) return;\n\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey;\n  if (!sessionKey) return;\n\n  const ctxPath = getContextPath(sessionKey);\n\n  let sessionData;\n  try {\n    sessionData = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(ctxPath, 'utf8'));\n  } catch {\n    // No context file yet — skip\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const messages = sessionData.messages || [];\n  if (messages.length < 6) return; // Nothing to compress\n\n  const tokens   = countSessionTokens(messages);\n  const limit    = config.maxTokens * config.threshold;\n\n  // Log each check (throttle by only logging when > 60%)\n  if (tokens > limit * 0.6) {\n    console.log(`[context-monitor] session=${sessionKey} tokens=${tokens}/${limit} (${Math.round(tokens/limit*100)}%)`);\n  }\n\n  if (tokens > limit) {\n    console.log(`[context-monitor] COMPACTING ${messages.length} messages...`);\n    const compacted = await compress(messages, config.preserveRecent);\n    sessionData.messages = compacted;\n    fs.writeFileSync(ctxPath, JSON.stringify(sessionData, null, 2));\n    console.log(`[context-monitor] Done: ${messages.length} → ${compacted.length} messages`);\n  }\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== 'message' && event.type !== 'agent') return;\n  if (event.action !== 'preprocessed' && event.action !== 'response') return;\n\n  try {\n    await handleEvent(event);\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`[context-monitor] ERROR: ${err.message}`);\n  }\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34396,"output":1376,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57637,"cost":{"input":0.0103188,"output":0.0016512,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0132819}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776486108533,"responseId":"063239dc11e1b7b18321020e7d4d3ff5"}}
