{"type":"message","id":"1f91836f","parentId":"373c588e","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:33:19.607Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No package.json in the v8 directory. So the v8 system wasn't fully set up with npm dependencies. Express and other modules aren't installed.\n\nThe full v8 system can't run without dependencies being installed. But we can create a lightweight 3102 router that:\n1. Provides the orchestration API (routes between 3103 and 3105)\n2. Exposes the scoring endpoint (which 3103 already provides as a standalone)\n3. Actually - 3103 and 3105 are already running as standalone services\n\nThe 3102 router's key value over just using 3103/3105 directly is the **orchestration layer** - it coordinates between them and provides the unified API. But since both services are already running and accessible...\n\n\nRather than trying to install dependencies and fix the full v8 system, I could write a lightweight Node.js router as a standalone service. Though I need to reconsider what 3102 actually does - looking at the spec, it's supposed to route between services, but 3103 and 3105 are already accessible individually, so maybe the real question is whether we actually need this middle layer or if we can work without it.\n\nLet me check if there's a package.json anywhere that has express listed as a dependency, or if express is installed globally.","thinkingSignature":"84c90dff949f00870012143c70d4f2c520e0bcfb39851bcc06c0921350f6e656"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jy540n20ccam_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 express 是否已安装（可能在 openclaw 目录）\nfind ~/.openclaw -name \"package.json\" -not -path \"*/node_modules/*\" 2>/dev/null | head -5\necho \"---\"\n# 检查全局或 openclaw node_modules 是否有 express\nls ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/node_modules/ 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"express|router\" | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46