{"type":"message","id":"123f9afb","parentId":"ab669025","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:34:40.772Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"3101 is running and healthy! Now let me move on to the 3102 Router. The question is: do we need it? Both 3103 and 3105 are running as standalone services. The hook calls 3103 and 3105 directly already.\n\nLooking at the spec again, 3102 is the \"internal microservice routing layer\" that hosts the scoring and classification logic. But in our setup, these are already running as standalone services:- 3103: scorer-server.js (our standalone wrapper)\n- 3105: classifier (already running via pi-agent-core subsystem)\n\nThe 3102 router was supposed to be the Express app that wraps these. But since they're already accessible... \n\n\nActually, I think the 3102 router is supposed to provide unified API over both services. But the question is whether we need it at all for the system to work.\n\nLooking at the spec more carefully: \"v8 Router 托管在 Gateway 进程内，端口 3102，是内部微服务路由层。\" - the router is supposed to be INSIDE the gateway process and provide routing to 3103/3105.\n\nSince both 3103 and 3105 are already accessible as standalone services, and the hook calls them directly, maybe we don't strictly need 3102 for basic functionality. The main value would be unified API and centralization.\n\nThe spec's architecture shows v8 Router (3102) as the central orchestrator that receives requests and routes to either the Scorer or Classifier. But since these are already running independently, I need to figure out whether the Router adds essential coordination logic that we can't get by calling them directly.\n\nLooking at what the router actually does - it handles task distribution and coordinates between the Scorer and Classifier, manages the flow between them, and provides a single entry point. For now, since 3103 and 3105 are already accessible and working, I could defer setting up 3102. But I should tackle the auto-router hook next since that's the piece most likely to help achieve full functionality.","thinkingSignature":"5e39150def5b93ba53610b30ded914368dbcf8cac884ec296554bbfd5148d64b"},{"type":"text","text":"\n3101 ✅。现在处理 **auto-router hook**——这个是最关键的自动派发核心，只有文档没有代码。\n\n先看它应该做什么：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hmdrj6yknwgx_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-router/HOOK.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50285,"output":489,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72639,"cost":{"input":0.0150855,"output":0.0005868,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0169842}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776486864547,"responseId":"06323ccf3fa6211af7153c7d910bba95"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0c67c4a","parentId":"123f9afb","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:34:41.358Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hmdrj6yknwgx_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"name: auto-router\ndescription: \"读取 ephemeral 中的 v8 评分结果，超过阈值时自动 fork 子 agent 处理，主 agent 返回任务已提交。\"\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\": {\n      \"emoji\": \"🔀\",\n      \"events\": [\"agent:preparing\"],\n      \"requires\": {\"bins\": [\"node\"], \"config\": []},\n      \"always\": true\n    }\n  }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776486881268}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c257b3c","parentId":"f0c67c4a","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:35:08.463Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The auto-router hook is supposed to:\n1. Listen on `agent:preparing` event\n2. Read ephemeral for v8 scoring results\n3. If score >= threshold, fork a sub-agent\n4. Main agent returns \"task submitted\"\n\nBut the `auto-score-classify` hook already does the `[AUTO_ROUTE]` injection on `message:preprocessed`. The auto-router was supposed to be a more sophisticated version that reads ephemeral data.\n\nThe problem: `agent:preparing` is a different event from `message:preprocessed`. Let me check if `agent:preparing` actually fires in the gateway.\n\nActually, looking at the hook system architecture doc I generated earlier, it lists:\n\n\n- `agent:bootstrap` - Agent startup\n- `agent:preparing` - Agent preparing to respond\n- `agent:response` - After response sent\n\nThe auto-router should fire on `agent:preparing`, read the score from the ephemeral store (written by auto-score-classify on `message:preprocessed`), and if the score is high enough, spawn a sub-agent while the main agent returns a \"task submitted\" message. But there's a timing issue: if auto-score-classify already injected `[AUTO_ROUTE]` on `message:preprocessed`, then by the time `agent:preparing` fires, the routing decision might already be made.\n\nActually, auto-score-classify runs on `message:preprocessed` which happens before the agent even starts thinking, so the prefix is already set before `agent:preparing` fires. This means auto-router would just be redundant—it's checking something that's already been decided. I need to look at the actual event sequence in the gateway to understand when each hook fires.\n\nSo the real issue is that auto-score-classify injects `[AUTO_ROUTE]` on the message itself before the agent processes it, which means the agent will see that prefix and spawn a sub-agent anyway. auto-router would run after that decision but can't actually prevent it. Given that auto-score-classify already handles the routing logic and works, maybe auto-router isn't needed—or I should implement it to read from ephemeral and log the decision instead of trying to override what's already been injected. the SOUL.md AUTO_ROUTE mechanism. That way if auto-score-classify ever fails, auto-router can catch it.\n\nBut the key question: does `agent:preparing` event actually fire in the current gateway? If it doesn't, auto-router would never trigger even if I implement it.\n\nLet me check what events are actually supported by looking at the gateway hook system code or logs. From the architecture doc I generated, it listed `agent:preparing` as a valid event. But let me verify.\n\nActually, let me just implement a minimal auto-router that:\n1. Tries to read ephemeral score data\n2. If score >= threshold, injects [AUTO_ROUTE] (as a failsafe for auto-score-classify)\n3. Logs what it found\n\nBut wait - if auto-score-classify already handles all messages with force mode (threshold=0), auto-router would just be redundant.\n\nActually, I think the right approach is:\n1. Keep auto-score-classify as the primary router (message:preprocessed)\n2. Make auto-router a failsafe that reads ephemeral and checks if [AUTO_ROUTE] was already injected\n3. If not injected but score >= threshold, inject it\n\nThe issue is: if auto-score-classify already force-injects [AUTO_ROUTE] for ALL messages, then there's nothing for auto-router to do as a failsafe. Let me reconsider what auto-router was originally supposed to do based on the spec: it should read ephemeral score, fork a sub-agent if the score is high enough, and the main agent should return \"task submitted\". This is actually a more sophisticated routing than what auto-score-classify does.\n\nBut this is exactly what the SOUL.md AUTO_ROUTE mechanism already does through sessions_spawn! The only difference is that auto-router would read from ephemeral rather than having auto-score-classify inject the prefix directly. So the real question is whether I should keep auto-score-classify with force mode or switch to a smarter two-hook system. Since auto-score-classify already works and the user confirmed the full chain is working, maybe I should focus on making auto-router a backup that reads the score from ephemeral and injects [AUTO_ROUTE] if auto-score-classify hasn't already done so.","thinkingSignature":"c3b839d03a3326b77ec3e126d4ecd4049a135704b176a7733cc9181a73489993"},{"type":"text","text":"auto-router 的价值：在 auto-score-classify 之后作为**二次校验**，基于 ephemeral 真实评分数据决定是否派发。现在 auto-score-classify 是强制模式（阈值=0），auto-router 可以成为真正的智能路由。\n\n实现前先确认 `agent:preparing` 事件是否在 gateway 中真实触发：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zx6nwy7tvcp1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"agent:preparing\\|agent_preparing\\|'agent'.*'preparing'\" /home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".map:\" | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50874,"output":1068,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73807,"cost":{"input":0.0152622,"output":0.0012816,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.017855700000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776486881360,"responseId":"06323cdf76228804fa5aead4f5ed8420"}}
