{"type":"message","id":"1ca507b0","parentId":"df5b09dc","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:35:40.371Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see that the gateway fires hooks for:\n- `agent:bootstrap`\n- `command:stop`\n- `command:reset` (from commands-reset-hooks)\n- `message:sent`\n- `message:preprocessed` (from the get-reply flow, which I saw earlier)\n\nBut I don't see `agent:preparing` being fired anywhere. So auto-router with `agent:preparing` won't work.\n\nThe key events that ARE fired:\n- `agent:bootstrap` ✅\n- `command:new`, `command:reset` ✅ (from commands-reset-hooks)\n- `message:preprocessed` ✅\n- `message:sent` ✅\n\n\n- `message:receive` - not confirmed yet\n\nSince `agent:preparing` doesn't exist, auto-router can't work as designed. I could either repurpose it to listen on `message:preprocessed` like auto-score-classify does, or drop it entirely given that auto-score-classify already handles routing. The best approach is probably to have auto-router fall back to `message:preprocessed` and read the ephemeral score to decide if it should override.\n\nThe issue is that both hooks would fire on the same event. To avoid conflicts, I should make auto-score-classify smarter by having it actually call the scorer and only inject [AUTO_ROUTE] when the score meets the threshold, rather than forcing it on everything. This way auto-router can step in as a secondary check when needed.\n\nThe real blocker is that scoring.js returns 0 when called directly via ESM import due to some module state issue, even though it works fine over HTTP. So I need to figure out why the HTTP scorer returns the right score but the direct import doesn't. I'm considering two approaches: either debug why the scorer returns 0 through direct imports and fix it, or make auto-score-classify use HTTP calls instead of direct imports. The HTTP approach is more reliable since that's how the actual scorer works, but I'd need to handle failures gracefully to avoid breaking the hook if the scorer becomes unavailable. Let me check how auto-score-classify is currently implemented.","thinkingSignature":"da890a4316407eeace80931e95aa10239d6fbb6e23c45e9c5ab4fd638de2223c"},{"type":"text","text":"`agent:preparing` 事件在 gateway 中**不存在**，auto-router 永远不会被触发。需要另找方案。\n\n核心问题：auto-score-classify 强制注入所有消息，没有真正调用 scorer。用 HTTP 方式调 scorer 会更可靠——实现一个真正基于评分的路由：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4ut9zy9zypwq_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":53250,"output":535,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75650,"cost":{"input":0.015975,"output":0.000642,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0179289}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776486927027,"responseId":"06323d0da9ba753907cda6f67288a7df"}}
{"type":"message","id":"224cf323","parentId":"1ca507b0","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:35:40.789Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4ut9zy9zypwq_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// auto-score-classify hook v8 - 强制派发所有任务（阈值=0）\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nconst SCORE_THRESHOLD = 0; // 所有消息都派发\nconst SCORER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\";\n\nfunction log(...args) {\n  console.log(`[hook] ${new Date().toISOString()} ${args.join(\" \")}`);\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") return;\n\n  const text = String(event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\");\n  if (!text.trim()) return;\n\n  if (text.startsWith(\"[AUTO_ROUTE]\")) {\n    log(\"SKIP: already has [AUTO_ROUTE]\");\n    return;\n  }\n\n  log(`MSG: \"${text.slice(0, 60)}\"`);\n\n  // 直接派发所有任务，不评分\n  event.context.bodyForAgent = `[AUTO_ROUTE] ${text}`;\n  log(`INJECTED [AUTO_ROUTE] (force mode, all tasks)`);\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776486940706}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5de0701","parentId":"224cf323","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:36:03.282Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update auto-score-classify to:\n1. Actually call the scorer via HTTP (the reliable way)\n2. Only inject [AUTO_ROUTE] if score >= 40\n3. If HTTP fails, fall back to NO_ROUTE (let main agent handle it normally)\n\nBut there's still the issue that scoring.js returns 0 via ESM import, and HTTP works fine. So I'll use HTTP.\n\nAlso, I should NOT force-inject all messages. The hook should:\n1. Send text to scorer via HTTP\n2. If score >= 40, inject [AUTO_ROUTE]\n\n\n3. If score < 40, let main agent handle it normally\n4. If HTTP fails, fall back gracefully\n\nBut wait—I need to be careful not to loop when the main agent already has [AUTO_ROUTE] injected, since that would trigger sessions_spawn and return NO_REPLY. I should add a guard to check for [AUTO_ROUTE] first and skip processing if it's already there.\n\nLooking at the execution order: auto-score-classify runs first on `message:preprocessed` and injects [AUTO_ROUTE], then the main agent SOUL.md rule sees it and spawns, then sessions_spawn returns NO_REPLY before agent:preparing would even fire. Since there's no `agent:preparing` event, auto-router is useless anyway—I'll focus on fixing auto-score-classify to use HTTP properly instead.","thinkingSignature":"529bd9f4406c7cf64f1152644bb07f93dec21c869a8e1a8e9fce68996c50e3ec"},{"type":"text","text":"把 auto-score-classify 改成**真正的评分模式**（HTTP 调用 scorer，阈值 40）：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f3hko4lrejg9_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js","content":"/**\n * auto-score-classify hook v9\n * 事件: message:preprocessed\n * 功能: 调用 3103 scorer，基于评分决定是否注入 [AUTO_ROUTE]\n * 降级: HTTP 失败时静默跳过，让主 agent 正常处理\n */\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nconst SCORE_THRESHOLD = 40;\nconst SCORER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\";\nconst TIMEOUT_MS = 5000;\n\nfunction log(...args) {\n  console.log(`[hook] ${new Date().toISOString()} ${args.join(\" \")}`);\n}\n\nfunction httpPost(url, body, timeoutMs = TIMEOUT_MS) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const timers = [];\n    const done = (val, err) => { timers.forEach(clearTimeout); resolve([val, err]); };\n\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: {\n          \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n          \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData),\n        },\n        timeout: timeoutMs,\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (c) => (data += c));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { done({ ok: true, body: JSON.parse(data) }, null); }\n          catch { done({ ok: false, body: data }, new Error(\"non-json\")); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"timeout\", () => { req.destroy(); done({ ok: false }, new Error(\"timeout\")); });\n    req.on(\"error\", (e) => done({ ok: false }, e));\n    timers.push(setTimeout(() => { req.destroy(); done({ ok: false }, new Error(\"timeout\")); }, timeoutMs));\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") return;\n\n  const text = String(event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\");\n  if (!text.trim()) return;\n  if (text.startsWith(\"[AUTO_ROUTE]\")) return;\n\n  log(`MSG: \"${text.slice(0, 60)}\"`);\n\n  // 调用 scorer\n  const [result, err] = await httpPost(SCORER_URL, { text });\n  if (!err && result.ok) {\n    const { score, recommendedStrategy } = result.body;\n    log(`SCORE: ${score} (threshold=${SCORE_THRESHOLD}) strategy=${recommendedStrategy}`);\n\n    if (score >= SCORE_THRESHOLD) {\n      event.context.bodyForAgent = `[AUTO_ROUTE] ${text}`;\n      log(`INJECTED [AUTO_ROUTE] score=${score}`);\n    } else {\n      log(`SKIP: score ${score} < ${SCORE_THRESHOLD}`);\n    }\n  } else {\n    // Scorer 不可用，降级：让主 agent 正常处理，不强制派发\n    log(`SCORER_ERROR: ${err?.message || \"unknown\"}, falling back to normal`);\n  }\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54056,"output":1047,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76968,"cost":{"input":0.0162168,"output":0.0012564,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.018785100000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776486940791,"responseId":"06323d1c06777845e6bf521f2b7829f1"}}
