{"type":"message","id":"627ad5d3","parentId":"184b0d67","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:37:43.867Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The 3102 Router uses express and many other modules. It needs a package.json to resolve dependencies. The issue is that the v8 directory doesn't have a package.json, so node can't find express.\n\nLet me create a minimal package.json for the v8 directory that uses the openclaw global node_modules. Or I could try running it with NODE_PATH set to the openclaw node_modules.\n\nActually, the simpler approach: run the index.js with NODE_PATH pointing to the openclaw node_modules where express is installed.","thinkingSignature":"7b6e760d206b1a2e7c2b26c997ef269111dc5a34ccb6abac5c427fce80a9db9b"},{"type":"text","text":"用 NODE_PATH 让 v8 找到 express：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v2n8dijou8n5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"NODE_PATH=/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/node_modules timeout 5 node ~/.openclaw/v8/src/index.js 2>&1 | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54792,"output":184,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76841,"cost":{"input":0.0164376,"output":0.0002208,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0179703}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776487057830,"responseId":"06323d903852e308cc8e9b1aa292341c"}}
