{"type":"message","id":"bce28154","parentId":"1df18570","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:40:59.762Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway is still using the OLD version of the hook (force mode with threshold=0) from before the restart. The latest logs show \"SCORE: 0 (threshold=40)\" from 12:37, which is the new version. But the latest messages (12:38) are returning score=0 even with the new scorer.\n\nWait - \"SCORE: 0 (threshold=40) strategy=DIRECT\" at 12:37:02 - this is the new version of the hook (which I just deployed). The message at 12:38:43 is also from the new version.\n\nBut the scorer was just restarted at 12:37 (after I killed 5572 and started 14063). \n\nSo the old scorer at 5572 must have been killed before that 12:37 message. But wait - the scorer and hook are separate processes, so the hook calling HTTP to the scorer could still be hitting a cached response or the old scorer instance if the restart didn't fully propagate.\n\nActually, I think I've found the real problem: the hook is using `http://127.0.0.1:3103` but the scorer might only be listening on IPv6 `::1` now, not `127.0.0.1`. That would explain why the hook can't reach the scorer even though it's supposedly restarted.","thinkingSignature":"830296d208a180a59aa0772bbb7fab40fb36126633b41ae09be00f8577065a6f"},{"type":"text","text":"scorer 重启后可能绑定变了。检查：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fqtintauaf03_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ss -tlnp 2>/dev/null | grep 3103"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":62594,"output":330,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84789,"cost":{"input":0.0187782,"output":0.000396,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0204861}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776487246951,"responseId":"06323e4e4163d8ae6575200f6086204c"}}
