{"type":"message","id":"014023bf","parentId":"470e0fcf","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:41:06.680Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Scorer is listening on 0.0.0.0:3103 - that's correct and should accept 127.0.0.1 connections.\n\nBut the hook is getting SCORE: 0. This is strange because I just tested the scorer directly and it returned non-zero scores.\n\nOh wait - I think I see the issue. The scorer-server.js was started in the background but maybe it's loading the OLD scoring.js because of module caching. Or maybe the scorer-server.js itself was updated but is running a cached version.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The scorer-server.js does `const { scoreTask } = require('./src/scoring/scoring.js')`. When I changed scoring.js on disk, the next time the module is loaded it will use the new code. But Node.js might cache the module. However, since the scorer was killed and restarted (not just the module being reloaded), it should load fresh.\n\n\nLet me verify what's actually in scoring.js right now.","thinkingSignature":"3b37541bf74a992211b77b7f6524459b446d7ca2c94c3e6a0f3efd36a291c471"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d4024f8vmnrz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"帮我写一个Python快速排序\"}'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":62985,"output":271,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85121,"cost":{"input":0.0188955,"output":0.0003252,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0205326}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776487260275,"responseId":"06323e5a17bb936f2642ca9cac065906"}}
