{"type":"message","id":"8f4e202c","parentId":"ea440b57","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:41:34.462Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The scorer-server.js correctly handles `body.prompt || body.text`. So `{ text: \"...\" }` should work fine.\n\nBut the hook is getting score=0. Let me think about what could be different...\n\nOh! I just realized something. The hook sends `{ text }` but maybe there's a timing issue. When I tested with curl, the scorer returned 33 for \"帮我写一个Python快速排序\". But the hook got 0.\n\nWait - let me look at the timing. The gateway restarted at 12:36. The scorer was restarted at 12:37 (after the gateway). So at 12:36 when the gateway started, the OLD scorer was still running on 5572. But 5572 was killed before 12:37.\n \nActually, the hook logs show \"SCORE: 0\" at 12:37:02, which is after the restart. But if the old scorer was killed before the new one started, that 0 could've come from a connection failure that the hook's error handler isn't catching properly. Though honestly, I should just test this directly by calling the hook's HTTP endpoint the same way the hook does.","thinkingSignature":"03f2310683c22eaf00f6bb84846c49bb412a221d31b960b4c9bf45b7020688cb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ror6o0sdp6u5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"先解决其它问题\"}'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":64151,"output":306,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86322,"cost":{"input":0.0192453,"output":0.0003672,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.020924400000000003}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776487285109,"responseId":"06323e73cd0101df8364a88b513844c2"}}
