{"type":"message","id":"c6cf432b","parentId":"8fa7dfc9","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:41:42.018Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"\"先解决其它问题\" gets score=0. That's the message that was just sent at 12:38. So the scorer correctly returns 0 for this simple message.\n\nSo the hook IS working correctly. It called the scorer, got back 0, and correctly did NOT inject AUTO_ROUTE. That's the expected behavior!\n\nThe system is working:\n1. Hook receives message \"先解决其它问题\"\n2. Hook calls scorer HTTP → score=0\n3. Hook sees 0 < 40 → SKIP (no AUTO_ROUTE injection)\n4. Main agent handles normally\n\nThis is the correct behavior! The scorer now correctly returns 0 for simple messages. The hook correctly respects the threshold.\n\n\nNow I'm realizing the distinction: the simpler quicksort task would score 33 (below the threshold, so main agent handles it), while the more complex architecture analysis scores 41 (above the threshold, triggering AUTO_ROUTE and subagent). Let me verify the quicksort score since the hook had returned 0 for it earlier.","thinkingSignature":"79d83c45274d1d8b84bc7ba8d17d58b01ac7db88b536b15721e1989807f28712"},{"type":"text","text":"hook 工作完全正确——\"先解决其它问题\"就是 score=0，不该派发。scorer 现在对中文评分正常了。\n\n验证更复杂任务的派发：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e2o2yayfzc2u_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"帮我写一个Python快速排序\"}'\necho \"\"\ncurl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"分析openclaw项目代码质量并生成重构建议\"}'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":64524,"output":364,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86753,"cost":{"input":0.019357199999999998,"output":0.0004368,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0211059}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776487294933,"responseId":"06323e7c51ce7bf1441030d9fdb