{"type":"message","id":"c86938af","parentId":"fce5d7aa","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:43:24.645Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking \"影响呢\" (what's the impact?) - probably asking about what problems the remaining missing items (3102 Router, agents.list) actually cause in practice. Let me think about this.\n\nThe user wants to know: what practical problems arise from the 3102 Router not running and agents.list being empty?\n\nLet me think about this:\n\n1. **3102 Router missing**: \n   - In the current architecture, the hook (auto-score-classify) directly calls 3103 scorer via HTTP\n   - 3102 was supposed to be a central routing layer that托管 3103 and 3105\n   - But since we bypass 3102 and call 3103 directly from the hook, the routing actually works fine\n   - The 3102's main value add was being a unified routing layer, but the hook system already provides this functionality\n\n2. **agents.list being empty**:\n   - The system is using default single-agent configuration (main)\n   - Multi-agent routing (coder/deep/fast agents) defined in spec is not available\n   - But: the AUTO_ROUTE mechanism spawns subagents via `sessions_spawn` which works fine\n   - The spec says there should be main/coder/deep/fast agents, but in practice, the main agent can handle everything since subagents are spawned as needed\n\nSo the practical impacts are minimal for the core functionality. The system works.\n\nBut wait - what the user is really asking might be: \"what are the consequences of NOT having these?\" or \"should we fix these?\" Let me be direct about this.\n\nThe most important practical impact is:\n- Without 3102 Router: some architectural features defined in the spec (like unified task orchestration, rate limiting, centralized monitoring) don't work, but the core hook-based routing still works\n- Without agents.list: the system uses default single-agent mode. The multi-agent specializations (coder for code tasks, deep for deep reasoning, etc.) don't exist as separate agents. But again, AUTO_ROUTE with subagents provides similar functionality\n\nSo the answer is: practically speaking, not much is broken because:\n1. The hook system (auto-score-classify) handles the routing job that 3102 was supposed to do\n2. The subagent spawning handles tasks that would have gone to specialized agents\n\nHowever, there's still value in addressing these gaps. I should explain the actual vs theoretical impacts to the user.","thinkingSignature":"f9eef4d7df90cb8065c4f3a1b4e6d8a34c65a1b1011bdce5e1eaf4a16790aedb"},{"type":"text","text":"### 思考\n\n用户问的是：3102 Router 和 agents.list 缺失，在实际使用中会造成什么问题。\n\n直接说实际影响：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dzvbnlqh8akp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 测试 auto_score_classify hook 对真实任务消息的派发行为\ncurl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"帮我分析这个项目的代码结构\"}'\necho \"\"\ncurl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"帮我创建一个网页爬虫\"}'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58,"output":657,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":62339,"totalTokens":84919,"cost":{"input":0.0000174,"output":0.0007884,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0.023377125000000002,"total":0.025494825000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776487384179,"responseId":"06323ed73f1dbc927641989f9143a494"}}
