{"type":"message","id":"158b0ed3","parentId":"3bd3987e","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:45:01.710Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now restart scorer and test. But first, let me also think about 3102 Router and agents.list while the scorer restarts.\n\nFor 3102 Router, the issue is dependencies: express, sqlite3, etc. The simplest fix would be to install the required npm packages in the v8 directory. But we need a package.json first.\n\nActually, wait. The v8 Router's core value - does it duplicate what hooks are already doing? The hook system already handles:\n- auto-score-classify: calls scorer directly\n- session-summary: LLM summarization\n- context-monitor: token counting\n\nThe 3102 Router would provide:\n- Unified HTTP API for all v8 services ( scorer + classifier + task management + scheduling)\n\n\n- Task persistence (TaskStore with sqlite3)\n- Rate limiting\n- Health checking\n- Metrics\n\nBut the problem is: without 3102, we just call scorer and classifier directly from hooks. The task management and persistence aren't implemented in any other component. So tasks aren't tracked persistently, there's no rate limiting, and the health/metrics infrastructure is missing. Let me just focus on getting 3102 running by creating a package.json and installing the needed dependencies.","thinkingSignature":"fa43927b22d5224097fedc90f4279fb3a5527c585abdc917392226235b3ace09"},{"type":"text","text":"scorer 补强的同时，处理 3102 Router——创建 package.json 并安装依赖：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yyivezp71x4t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep \"14063\\|scorer\" | grep -v grep | awk '{print $2}'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":66424,"output":314,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88603,"cost":{"input":0.0199272,"output":0.0003768,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0216159}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776487489733,"responseI