{"type":"message","id":"563fe737","parentId":"3f13b97c","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:47:54.819Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me take a different approach. Instead of trying to configure agents.list (which I don't have clear documentation for), let me focus on what CAN be done:\n\n1. ✅ scoring patterns - done\n2. ❌ 3102 Router - can't fix (sqlite3 dependency issue)\n3. agents.list - unknown schema, hard to fix without docs\n4. auto-router hook - event doesn't exist, but we can improve auto-score-classify to do what it was supposed to do\n5. ephemeral real-time writing - need to investigate\n\nLet me look at the ephemeral issue more carefully. The ephemeral files stopped being written after 10:58 AM today. Let me check what's supposed to write to them and why it stopped.\n\n\nI think I found the issue - ephemeral is written by the self-improvement hook when the agent calls certain memory functions, but since we're using sessions_spawn for subagents, that hook might not be running in the right context. The session-summary hook should trigger on /new or /reset commands and write to memory instead, but if we're not using those commands, ephemeral won't get updated. I should focus on the ephemeral problem and then improve the auto-score-classify hook with better scoring and routing logic.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the ephemeral directory is just a fallback - the main path is session-summary writing to memory/, which is already working (session-summary hook is deployed). But session-summary only runs at /new, not on every message. That's by design. The ephemeral writing is happening through a hook, so I need to understand which hook is actually responsible for it and whether it's being triggered correctly.\n\nThe real issue is that I may have already fixed this problem earlier today - the gateway is running with 7 handlers loaded, which was the fix. But the user wants comprehensive verification, so I should systematically check what's actually broken versus what I think I've already solved. For the remaining items, the auto-score-classify hook can be enhanced to replace the auto-router logic since that event doesn't exist in the gateway.","thinkingSignature":"f69e56740fdbd6c10867acb32119256676a53e627fa050673bf1975e24353a3d"},{"type":"text","text":"3102 缺 sqlite3 无法补装，先放过去。处理 **auto-router**——用它替代 `agent:preparing` 事件（该事件不存在），在 auto-score-classify 里实现 auto-router 的核心逻辑：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8pamt745h2mw_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":71880,"output":497,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94242,"cost":{"input":0.021564,"output":0.0005964,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0234723}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776487657941,"responseId":"06323fe90cd2081d6bc3346d245eef24"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fdcbca89","parentId":"563fe737","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:47:55.293Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8pamt745h2mw_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * auto-score-classify hook v9\n * 事件: message:preprocessed\n * 功能: 调用 3103 scorer，基于评分决定是否注入 [AUTO_ROUTE]\n * 降级: HTTP 失败时静默跳过，让主 agent 正常处理\n */\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nconst SCORE_THRESHOLD = 40;\nconst SCORER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\";\nconst TIMEOUT_MS = 5000;\n\nfunction log(...args) {\n  console.log(`[hook] ${new Date().toISOString()} ${args.join(\" \")}`);\n}\n\nfunction httpPost(url, body, timeoutMs = TIMEOUT_MS) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const timers = [];\n    const done = (val, err) => { timers.forEach(clearTimeout); resolve([val, err]); };\n\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: {\n          \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n          \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData),\n        },\n        timeout: timeoutMs,\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (c) => (data += c));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { done({ ok: true, body: JSON.parse(data) }, null); }\n          catch { done({ ok: false, body: data }, new Error(\"non-json\")); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"timeout\", () => { req.destroy(); done({ ok: false }, new Error(\"timeout\")); });\n    req.on(\"error\", (e) => done({ ok: false }, e));\n    timers.push(setTimeout(() => { req.destroy(); done({ ok: false }, new Error(\"timeout\")); }, timeoutMs));\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") return;\n\n  const text = String(event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\");\n  if (!text.trim()) return;\n  if (text.startsWith(\"[AUTO_ROUTE]\")) return;\n\n  log(`MSG: \"${text.slice(0, 60)}\"`);\n\n  // 调用 scorer\n  const [result, err] = await httpPost(SCORER_URL, { text });\n  if (!err && result.ok) {\n    const { score, recommendedStrategy } = result.body;\n    log(`SCORE: ${score} (threshold=${SCORE_THRESHOLD}) strategy=${recommendedStrategy}`);\n\n    if (score >= SCORE_THRESHOLD) {\n      event.context.bodyForAgent = `[AUTO_ROUTE] ${text}`;\n      log(`INJECTED [AUTO_ROUTE] score=${score}`);\n    } else {\n      log(`SKIP: score ${score} < ${SCORE_THRESHOLD}`);\n    }\n  } else {\n    // Scorer 不可用，降级：让主 agent 正常处理，不强制派发\n    log(`SCORER_ERROR: ${err?.message || \"unknown\"}, falling back to normal`);\n  }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776487675213}}
{"type":"message","id":"5ebfa446","parentId":"fdcbca89","timestamp":"2026-04-18T04:48:12.752Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The auto-score-classify hook is already doing what auto-router was supposed to do. The current v9 implementation:\n1. Calls scorer via HTTP\n2. Based on score >= 40, injects [AUTO_ROUTE]\n3. Logs the score and strategy\n\nThis is exactly the auto-router logic. The only difference is that auto-router was supposed to also write the scoring result to ephemeral for later reference. Let me add that capability to make it truly complete.\n\nActually, I should also add ephemeral writing to auto-score-classify, so the scoring results are persisted for debugging and for the session-summary to pick up later.\n\nLet me update auto-score-classify to also write to ephemeral:","thinkingSignature":"83a52e854b72e89b0e5b900c90e4b7e805afb51f0b5a7712c44b515712876eaa"},{"type":"text","text":"auto-score-classify 已经承担了 auto-router 的职责。现在升级它，让它同时把评分结果写入 ephemeral（供 session-summary 和人工调试用）：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h0dinut9qdg3_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js","content":"/**\n * auto-score-classify hook v10\n * 事件: message:preprocessed\n * 功能:\n *   1. 调用 3103 scorer，基于评分决定是否注入 [AUTO_ROUTE]\n *   2. 将评分结果写入 ephemeral/*.jsonl（供 session-summary 和调试用）\n * 降级: Scorer 不可用时静默跳过，让主 agent 正常处理\n */\nimport http from \"node:http\";\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\n\nconst SCORE_THRESHOLD = 40;\nconst SCORER_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\";\nconst TIMEOUT_MS = 5000;\nconst EPHEMERAL_DIR = \"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral\";\n\nfunction log(...args) {\n  console.log(`[hook] ${new Date().toISOString()} ${args.join(\" \")}`);\n}\n\nfunction httpPost(url, body, timeoutMs = TIMEOUT_MS) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const timers = [];\n    const done = (val, err) => { timers.forEach(clearTimeout); resolve([val, err]); };\n\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: {\n          \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n          \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData),\n        },\n        timeout: timeoutMs,\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (c) => (data += c));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { done({ ok: true, body: JSON.parse(data) }, null); }\n          catch { done({ ok: false, body: data }, new Error(\"non-json\")); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"timeout\", () => { req.destroy(); done({ ok: false }, new Error(\"timeout\")); });\n    req.on(\"error\", (e) => done({ ok: false }, e));\n    timers.push(setTimeout(() => { req.destroy(); done({ ok: false }, new Error(\"timeout\")); }, timeoutMs));\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nfunction writeEphemeral(sessionKey, text, score, strategy, factors) {\n  try {\n    const today = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10); // YYYY-MM-DD\n    const hour = String(new Date().getHours()).padStart(2, \"0\");\n    const filePath = path.join(EPHEMERAL_DIR, `${today}-${hour}.jsonl`);\n\n    const entry = {\n      timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n      sessionKey,\n      scene: \"task\",\n      score,\n      strategy,\n      factors,\n      preview: text.slice(0, 100),\n    };\n\n    const line = JSON.stringify(entry) + \"\\n\";\n    fs.appendFileSync(filePath, line, \"utf8\");\n    log(`EPHEMERAL written: ${filePath}`);\n  } catch (err) {\n    log(`EPHEMERAL_WRITE_ERROR: ${err.message}`);\n  }\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") return;\n\n  const text = String(event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\");\n  if (!text.trim()) return;\n  if (text.startsWith(\"[AUTO_ROUTE]\")) return;\n\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"unknown\";\n\n  // 调用 scorer\n  const [result, err] = await httpPost(SCORER_URL, { text });\n  if (!err && result.ok) {\n    const { score, recommendedStrategy, factors } = result.body;\n    log(`SCORE: ${score} (threshold=${SCORE_THRESHOLD}) strategy=${recommendedStrategy}`);\n\n    // 写入 ephemeral\n    writeEphemeral(sessionKey, text, score, recommendedStrategy, factors);\n\n    if (score >= SCORE_THRESHOLD) {\n      event.context.bodyForAgent = `[AUTO_ROUTE] ${text}`;\n      log(`INJECTED [AUTO_ROUTE] score=${score}`);\n    } else {\n      log(`SKIP: score ${score} < ${SCORE_THRESHOLD}`);\n    }\n  } else {\n    log(`SCORER_ERROR: ${err?.message || \"unknown\"}, falling back to normal`);\n  }\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":73067,"output":1158,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96090,"cost":{"input":0.021920099999999998,"output":0.0013896,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0246216}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776487675295,"responseId":"06323ff974b08b18b8dc7bf2d46b2f36"}}
