{"type":"message","id":"784749ec","parentId":"5ee366d9","timestamp":"2026-04-18T08:52:09.274Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's a syntax error! The `, (\"` that appeared in my edit was real, not an artifact. The file shows:\n```javascript\n  }, ( (proxyRes) => {\n```\n\nBut it should be:\n```javascript\n  }, (proxyRes) => {\n```\n\nAlso the `path` variable is `undefined` because the URL constructor is failing. The issue is `const url = new URL(req.url, ...)` - but when called by curl, `req.url` might be just `/health` or `/api/score`. Let me check if `new URL('/health', 'http://localhost')` works.\n\nActually wait, looking more carefully at the error: `http://127.0.0.1:3103undefined`. \n\nSo `path` is literally the string `\"undefined\"` rather than an actual path, which means `url.pathname` is returning undefined and I'm concatenating it as a string instead of passing the proper path value to the function. I think the issue is that my edit removed the fourth argument from the `proxy(req, res, CLASSIFIER_URL)` call without updating the function signature. Let me check the router-server.js file to see what's actually there versus what I thought I changed.","thinkingSignature":"3392f65146be1e6874517ff309c49e683fef4677f6478540a470842e85c5497d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fc59irymgke9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat -n /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scripts/router-server.js | head -60"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":92586,"output":297,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":114748,"cost":{"input":0.0277758,"output":0.0003564,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0294441}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776502320162,"responseId":"0632792f51580c78816dc264368e8567"}}
{"type":"message","id":"aaef3273","parentId":"784749ec","timestamp":"2026-04-18T08:52:09.818Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fc59irymgke9_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1\t#!/usr/bin/env node\n     2\t/**\n     3\t * v8 Router - Minimal HTTP router on port 3102\n     4\t * Proxies /api/score → 3103 (scorer)\n     5\t * Proxies /classify  → 3105 (classifier)\n     6\t * Health check on /health\n     7\t */\n     8\tconst http = require('http');\n     9\t\n    10\tconst SCORER_URL = 'http://127.0.0.1:3103';\n    11\tconst CLASSIFIER_URL = 'http://127.0.0.1:3105';\n    12\tconst PORT = 3102;\n    13\t\n    14\tfunction proxy(req, res, target, path) {\n    15\t  const headers = { ...req.headers };\n    16\t  delete headers['host'];\n    17\t  delete headers['connection'];\n    18\t  const proxyReq = http.request(target + path, {\n    19\t    method: req.method,\n    20\t    headers,\n    21\t  }, ( (proxyRes) => {\n    22\t    res.writeHead(proxyRes.statusCode, proxyRes.headers);\n    23\t    proxyRes.pipe(res);\n    24\t  });\n    25\t  proxyReq.on('error', (e) => {\n    26\t    res.writeHead(502);\n    27\t    res.end(JSON.stringify({ error: e.message }));\n    28\t  });\n    29\t  req.pipe(proxyReq);\n    30\t}\n    31\t\n    32\tconst server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\n    33\t  // CORS\n    34\t  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');\n    35\t  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, OPTIONS');\n    36\t  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type');\n    37\t\n    38\t  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') { res.writeHead(204); res.end(); return; }\n    39\t\n    40\t  const url = new URL(req.url, `http://${req.headers.host}`);\n    41\t\n    42\t  if (url.pathname === '/health') {\n    43\t    res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n    44\t    res.end(JSON.stringify({ status: 'ok', service: 'v8-router', port: PORT }));\n    45\t    return;\n    46\t  }\n    47\t\n    48\t  if (url.pathname === '/api/score' || url.pathname === '/score') {\n    49\t    proxy(req, res, SCORER_URL, url.pathname);\n    50\t    return;\n    51\t  }\n    52\t\n    53\t  if (url.pathname === '/classify') {\n    54\t    proxy(req, res, CLASSIFIER_URL, url.pathname);\n    55\t    return;\n    56\t  }\n    57\t\n    58\t  res.writeHead(404);\n    59\t  res.end(JSON.stringify({ error: 'Not found', pathname: url.pathname }));\n    60\t});"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":263,"aggregated":"1\t#!/usr/bin/env node\n     2\t/**\n     3\t * v8 Router - Minimal HTTP router on port 3102\n     4\t * Proxies /api/score → 3103 (scorer)\n     5\t * Proxies /classify  → 3105 (classifier)\n     6\t * Health check on /health\n     7\t */\n     8\tconst http = require('http');\n     9\t\n    10\tconst SCORER_URL = 'http://127.0.0.1:3103';\n    11\tconst CLASSIFIER_URL = 'http://127.0.0.1:3105';\n    12\tconst PORT = 3102;\n    13\t\n    14\tfunction proxy(req, res, target, path) {\n    15\t  const headers = { ...req.headers };\n    16\t  delete headers['host'];\n    17\t  delete headers['connection'];\n    18\t  const proxyReq = http.request(target + path, {\n    19\t    method: req.method,\n    20\t    headers,\n    21\t  }, ( (proxyRes) => {\n    22\t    res.writeHead(proxyRes.statusCode, proxyRes.headers);\n    23\t    proxyRes.pipe(res);\n    24\t  });\n    25\t  proxyReq.on('error', (e) => {\n    26\t    res.writeHead(502);\n    27\t    res.end(JSON.stringify({ error: e.message }));\n    28\t  });\n    29\t  req.pipe(proxyReq);\n    30\t}\n    31\t\n    32\tconst server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\n    33\t  // CORS\n    34\t  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');\n    35\t  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, OPTIONS');\n    36\t  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type');\n    37\t\n    38\t  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') { res.writeHead(204); res.end(); return; }\n    39\t\n    40\t  const url = new URL(req.url, `http://${req.headers.host}`);\n    41\t\n    42\t  if (url.pathname === '/health') {\n    43\t    res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n    44\t    res.end(JSON.stringify({ status: 'ok', service: 'v8-router', port: PORT }));\n    45\t    return;\n    46\t  }\n    47\t\n    48\t  if (url.pathname === '/api/score' || url.pathname === '/score') {\n    49\t    proxy(req, res, SCORER_URL, url.pathname);\n    50\t    return;\n    51\t  }\n    52\t\n    53\t  if (url.pathname === '/classify') {\n    54\t    proxy(req, res, CLASSIFIER_URL, url.pathname);\n    55\t    return;\n    56\t  }\n    57\t\n    58\t  res.writeHead(404);\n    59\t  res.end(JSON.stringify({ error: 'Not found', pathname: url.pathname }));\n    60\t});","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776502329708}}
