{"type":"message","id":"e92c9bbd","parentId":"e505cf6e","timestamp":"2026-04-18T08:53:16.110Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the `agents.list` key is missing from the config. I need to add it. Looking at the spec doc, agents.list should contain entries for main/coder/deep/fast/thinker etc.\n\nBut actually, this is a complex configuration that requires understanding the full agent config schema. The key thing is that subagents are spawned via `sessions_spawn` without needing a pre-configured agent list.\n\nHowever, to properly address the \"全面跑通\" requirement, I should add at least a basic agent list. Let me look at what agent configs exist in the agents directory to get the right format.\n\nThe agents directory at `~/.openclaw/agents/` has subdirectories like `main/`, `coder/`, `codex/`, `deep/`, `deep_agent/`, `fast/`, `fast_agent/`, `thinker/`. But these don't have `agent.json` config files.\n\nActually, looking more carefully - the agents are defined by directory structure, and the openclaw.json `agents.list` configures which agents are available to the system. \n\nWithout proper documentation on the expected schema format, configuring this could easily break the system. For now, the `sessions_spawn` approach handles subagent creation fine, so I'll skip modifying agents.list and focus on documenting what would need to be configured here rather than risking a misconfiguration.\n\nActually, let me check the workspace docs for any clues about the agents.list schema.","thinkingSignature":"1c5baf577fb26c5db21d26be71cdc0ab40b28e32a158fac273da361ac98386e6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8297ruvukmf9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw -name \"*.md\" -not -path \"*/node_modules/*\" 2>/dev/null | xargs grep -l \"agents.list\\|agents\\.list\\|\\\"list\\\":\" 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":95396,"output":372,"cacheRea