{"type":"message","id":"a59881e3","parentId":"474789f3","timestamp":"2026-04-18T09:08:48.949Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The latest gateway loads show \"loaded 7 internal hook handlers\" and NO errors about context-monitor. That means the HOOK.md fix worked - context-monitor IS being loaded correctly now. The \"no events defined\" warning was from the old gateway load before the HOOK.md was fixed.\n\nLet me confirm the context-monitor handler is actually running and receiving events. I can check if there are any context-monitor log entries after the 12:48 restart.\n\nActually, looking at the earlier log output, I saw this in the old logs:\n```\n{\"1\":\"Hook 'context-monitor' has no events defined in metadata\",\"_meta\":{\"date\":\"2026-04-18T04:24:20.670Z\"...}}\n\n\n```\n\nThe timestamps show the gateway was restarted around 12:24-12:36-12:48-12:55, and context-monitor only appears in those early logs with the metadata error. After the latest restart at 12:55, there's no error for context-monitor, which confirms the hook is now being loaded properly.\n\nBut I'm seeing 7 handlers loaded even though there should be 8 - self-improvement, context-hook, auto-score-classify, session-summary, context-monitor, command-logger, and context_hook (legacy) should add up to 7, but that's actually 7 already. Let me verify what that 8th handler actually is.\n\n```","thinkingSignature":"5372c6e6d4e4884817c91ff8c18e55125570642febe6e5a85eb0d6ce9eea0ba9"},{"type":"text","text":"12:48 和 12:55 的加载日志都显示 7 handlers，且**没有** context-monitor 报错。说明 HOOK.md 修复后它已正确加载。\n\n但 3108 还没查。先查 3108 是什么：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ykckfwg8b514_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"3108\\|scene.*classifier\\|v8.*classifier\" /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-18.log 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"gateway\\|subsystem\" | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":103386,"output":417,