{"type":"message","id":"8e5d3a45","parentId":"273b17ce","timestamp":"2026-04-18T09:46:31.283Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the INJECTED entries:1. 16:53 - INJECTED score=67 (user message - real task, CORRECT)\n2. 17:05 - INJECTED score=41 (user message about \"全落地\" - CORRECT)\n3. 17:27:45 - INJECTED score=41 - what was the message at this time? The heartbeat poll came at 17:27. This is the one that says \"Read HEARTBEAT.md\" and it's MY OWN REPLY that got scored! That's the bug - when I return HEARTBEAT_OK, my own reply goes through the hook scoring.Wait - actually let me think about this more carefully. \n\nThe 17:27 entry scored a HEARTBEAT message that came through the gateway, and that's actually a real problem. But looking at the ephemeral records more closely, I notice the preview text for the HEARTBEAT entry doesn't show \"HEARTBEAT_OK\" at all - it starts with \"Read HEARTBEAT.md\" instead. So the preview shown at 17:05 is actually for a user message, not my reply, which means I need to reconsider what's being logged and when. I'm tracing through the timeline more carefully now. The 17:27 heartbeat poll at T6 scored 41 and injected [AUTO_ROUTE], which should trigger a subagent spawn that returns HEARTBEAT_OK. But then at T7, another message appears scoring 24 and skipping, when the preview actually shows the [AUTO_ROUTE] injected message from T6. The sequence is: HEARTBEAT poll at 17:27 scored 41 and got INJECTED with [AUTO_ROUTE], causing a subagent spawn, then the response HEARTBEAT_OK came back at 17:27:45. Then at 17:45 a user message scored 24 and skipped, but the ephemeral preview shows \"[AUTO_ROUTE]\" content - this doesn't quite make sense.\n\nI think what's happening is that messages prefixed with [AUTO_ROUTE] are being injected back into the system and scored again, creating duplicate entries in the ephemeral log. The subagent spawned at 17:27 is likely sending its response through sessions_send, which re-injects it into the main session where it gets scored a second time.\n\nThe real problem is that the hook isn't filtering out heartbeat messages, so they're being processed as regular tasks and spawning unnecessary subagents. I need to add filters for heartbeat content, system commands like /new and /reset, and messages that already have the [AUTO_ROUTE] prefix to prevent this re-injection cycle.","thinkingSignature":"0c1ef1903f8c6553e9310413e546248bc739a0ce44cc36650180ebd8019bc45b"},{"type":"text","text":"发现严重问题：**HEARTBEAT 被当作任务派发**（17:27:45 得分为 41 → spawn 子 agent）。这是 bug，需要修复。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6ivxjd9bjw6g_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js","offset":60,"limit":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":121027,"output":646,"cacheRead":21865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":143538,"cost":{"input":0.036308099999999996,"output":0.0007752,"cacheRead":0.0013119,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03839519999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776505566491,"responseId":"063285deb1023bd018bc53f1b82d8f91"}}
